WEBVTT

1
00:00:22.234 --> 00:00:25.134
<font color="#ff8000">Subtitles by Prospero</font>
<font color="#8080ff">prospero.13t@gmail.com</font>

2
00:00:25.235 --> 00:00:30.823
I have the feeling that I should
be angry with this child...

3
00:00:31.407 --> 00:00:35.495
with this childish young thing
or I shouldn't forgive her...

4
00:00:35.662 --> 00:00:40.124
for not realizing the horrors.
the monster. before it was too late.

5
00:00:40.333 --> 00:00:43.836
For not realizing what
she was getting into.

6
00:00:44.170 --> 00:00:47.465
How could I have agreed to it
so impulsively?

7
00:00:47.632 --> 00:00:51.427
I was not an enthusiastic Nazi.

8
00:00:51.636 --> 00:00:55.598
When I came to Berlin.
I could have said. "No.

9
00:00:55.765 --> 00:01:01.771
I won't take part. I don't want
to be sent to the Führer HQ".

10
00:01:02.063 --> 00:01:07.360
But I didn't say no.
Curiosity got the better of me.

11
00:01:07.569 --> 00:01:10.154
And I simply never thought...

12
00:01:10.280 --> 00:01:13.700
that fate would take me somewhere
I'd never really wanted to be.

13
00:01:14.075 --> 00:01:19.497
And yet. it's very hard
to forgive myself for doing it.

14
00:01:26.379 --> 00:01:28.381
The ladies are here.

15
00:01:29.465 --> 00:01:31.217
Military District II has confirmed.

16
00:01:31.467 --> 00:01:33.177
You may pass.

17
00:02:03.499 --> 00:02:06.085
<font color="#808000">[FUHRER'S HEADQUARTERS "WOLFSSCHANZE]</font>

18
00:02:06.252 --> 00:02:08.296
<font color="#808000">[RASTENBURG. EAST PRUSSIA. NOVEMBER 1942]</font>

19
00:02:11.507 --> 00:02:13.801
Please take a seat. ladies.

20
00:02:15.386 --> 00:02:17.764
I must ask you to wait
a few minutes.

21
00:02:18.139 --> 00:02:20.767
The Führer is feeding his dog.
He will be with you shortly.

22
00:02:22.310 --> 00:02:27.148
Tell me... How do we...
How does one greet the Führer?

23
00:02:28.066 --> 00:02:32.111
The Fuhrer will speak to you first.
and you just say. "Heil. my Fuhrer".

24
00:02:32.779 --> 00:02:34.113
What about the Nazi salute?

25
00:02:35.323 --> 00:02:39.327
That won't be necessary. The Führer
isn't recruiting you as soldiers...

26
00:02:39.786 --> 00:02:42.330
he's looking for a secretary.

27
00:02:42.538 --> 00:02:44.082
Behave normally.

28
00:02:44.248 --> 00:02:48.086
Just be natural. I'll ask him
if he has time for you now.

29
00:02:52.507 --> 00:02:55.551
My Führer. the ladies from Berlin are here.

30
00:03:14.278 --> 00:03:19.575
I'd like to thank you for coming
in the middle of the night. ladies.

31
00:03:20.827 --> 00:03:25.581
But in war. we aren't always
masters of our own time.

32
00:03:27.834 --> 00:03:31.587
May I ask your name?
Margarethe Lorenz. Heil. my Führer.

33
00:03:31.754 --> 00:03:34.382
Where are you from?
Fulda. Heil. my Führer.

34
00:03:34.590 --> 00:03:38.177
And you?
Ursula Puttkammer. Heil. my Führer.

35
00:03:38.302 --> 00:03:42.223
Leave that out. child.
Tell me where you're from.

36
00:03:42.390 --> 00:03:44.600
Frankfurt on the Main. my Führer.

37
00:03:46.853 --> 00:03:49.564
I'm Hannah Potrovsky.
born and raised in Berlin.

38
00:03:49.689 --> 00:03:52.608
To be precise. I come from Pankow.

39
00:03:52.859 --> 00:03:56.571
Hedwig Brandt from Crailsheim. Swabia.

40
00:03:57.405 --> 00:03:58.406
And you?

41
00:03:58.781 --> 00:04:01.409
Traudl Humps. I come from Munich.

42
00:04:03.786 --> 00:04:06.247
A Munich girl.

43
00:04:12.795 --> 00:04:17.091
So. Fräulein Humps. shall we start?

44
00:04:27.477 --> 00:04:31.898
Blondi won't hurt you.
She has a very sharp mind.

45
00:04:32.231 --> 00:04:35.651
In fact. she's more clever
than most people are.

46
00:04:39.614 --> 00:04:42.617
Just make yourself comfortable.

47
00:04:43.826 --> 00:04:47.246
Don't be nervous. I make so
many mistakes when I dictate...

48
00:04:47.371 --> 00:04:51.292
you'll never make as many as I do.

49
00:05:00.676 --> 00:05:02.804
You're quite young.

50
00:05:03.513 --> 00:05:06.682
How old are you?
22. my Führer.

51
00:05:12.104 --> 00:05:14.816
"My national comrades...

52
00:05:15.107 --> 00:05:19.487
German men and women.
members of the Party...

53
00:05:20.279 --> 00:05:23.574
it is. I believe. a rare thing...

54
00:05:24.116 --> 00:05:28.538
that a man can stand before...

55
00:05:28.704 --> 00:05:32.542
his old supporters after
20 years in office...

56
00:05:32.834 --> 00:05:36.337
and that during those 20 years...

57
00:05:36.504 --> 00:05:41.008
he did not have to modify
his policies whatsoever."

58
00:05:55.147 --> 00:05:59.569
I suggest that we try it again.

59
00:06:11.163 --> 00:06:13.749
I made it!
He gave me a job!

60
00:06:22.717 --> 00:06:26.304
<font color="#808000">[BERLIN. APRIL 20. 1945]</font>
<font color="#808000">ADOLF HITLER'S 56TH BIRTHDAY</font>

61
00:06:26.762 --> 00:06:29.015
<font color="#808000">[TWO AND A HALF YEARS LATER]</font>

62
00:06:35.187 --> 00:06:36.439
Duck!

63
00:06:40.192 --> 00:06:44.447
Keep moving!
Get off the street!

64
00:06:46.616 --> 00:06:47.783
Duck!

65
00:07:00.630 --> 00:07:01.756
That's artillery.

66
00:07:02.089 --> 00:07:05.635
Are you crazy?
How could they be firing artillery?

67
00:07:06.469 --> 00:07:10.264
Frau Junge. you're right!
Those aren't bombs. it's artillery!

68
00:07:10.431 --> 00:07:12.600
It's the Russians.

69
00:07:12.624 --> 00:07:14.624
What a fine birthday present!

70
00:07:19.482 --> 00:07:22.109
What's going on. Burgdorf?
Where's that gunfire coming from?

71
00:07:22.234 --> 00:07:24.820
Happy birthday. my Führer.

72
00:07:25.196 --> 00:07:28.074
Central Berlin is being shelled...

73
00:07:28.240 --> 00:07:30.451
from the Brandenburg Gate
to the Reichstag...

74
00:07:30.660 --> 00:07:34.455
up to Friedrichstrasse Station.
Where from?

75
00:07:34.622 --> 00:07:39.251
No news yet. Koller's on the line.
Give him to me.

76
00:07:39.543 --> 00:07:43.673
Koller. do you realize Berlin
is under artillery fire?

77
00:07:44.090 --> 00:07:47.510
No. Don't tell me you can't hear it!

78
00:07:47.802 --> 00:07:50.846
No. I'm at Werder Game Park.
<i>Berlin is in uproar!</i>

79
00:07:51.263 --> 00:07:54.392
The Russians have taken
a rail bridge on the Oder.

80
00:07:54.558 --> 00:07:57.144
They've got no railway
batteries near the Oder.

81
00:07:58.813 --> 00:08:00.523
That's not long-range gunfire.

82
00:08:00.690 --> 00:08:04.694
<i>The flak command post in the Zoo-bunker...</i>

83
00:08:04.986 --> 00:08:08.114
claims the guns have a caliber
of just 10 to 12 cm.

84
00:08:08.280 --> 00:08:10.533
The Russian battery is now in Marzahn.

85
00:08:10.700 --> 00:08:13.661
That's only 12 kilometers
from the city center!

86
00:08:13.828 --> 00:08:15.538
Are the Russians that close?

87
00:08:15.705 --> 00:08:19.542
The entire air force command
should be hanged!

88
00:08:21.293 --> 00:08:23.838
Outrageous!
Outrageous!

89
00:08:24.171 --> 00:08:27.174
The Russians are just 12 kilometers
from the city center...

90
00:08:27.341 --> 00:08:30.720
and nobody told me!
I had to ask!

91
00:08:31.846 --> 00:08:36.434
Perhaps it's long-range gunfire.
You mentioned a railway battery...

92
00:08:36.726 --> 00:08:38.519
Nonsense!

93
00:08:44.191 --> 00:08:48.446
Himmler is such a pompous clown!
Big shots!

94
00:08:48.612 --> 00:08:52.992
Big shots everywhere! It makes
me sick just looking at them!

95
00:08:55.411 --> 00:08:58.080
The Führer is putting "Clausewitz"
into operation today.

96
00:08:58.247 --> 00:09:02.752
Berlin as a front-line city...
He won't be able to hold the city.

97
00:09:03.085 --> 00:09:07.757
If he stays. he'll take the Reich
down. We have to talk him out of it.

98
00:09:08.758 --> 00:09:10.760
Speak to Hewel.

99
00:09:11.093 --> 00:09:14.096
He's the only diplomat
who can still influence him.

100
00:09:14.263 --> 00:09:17.016
Believe me. it's no use.

101
00:09:18.142 --> 00:09:21.020
Then talk to your sister-in-law.

102
00:09:21.353 --> 00:09:24.565
Why not? You're married
to Eva Braun's sister...

103
00:09:24.690 --> 00:09:28.152
so you're "related" to the Führer.
We have to try everything.

104
00:09:28.527 --> 00:09:30.654
Berlin is practically surrounded by the Russians.

105
00:09:31.030 --> 00:09:33.365
You're young.
You'll be a father soon.

106
00:09:33.783 --> 00:09:36.786
Do you want to die in Berlin?
Certainly not.

107
00:09:42.166 --> 00:09:44.585
Gentlemen. the Führer!

108
00:09:54.595 --> 00:09:59.391
Everything out and quick!
We're leaving in two hours.

109
00:10:07.149 --> 00:10:11.278
What's going on?
We're leaving. Haven't you heard?

110
00:10:12.071 --> 00:10:13.697
"Clausewitz" is in effect.

111
00:10:14.031 --> 00:10:17.743
All government departments and
Wehrmacht offices will leave Berlin.

112
00:10:18.160 --> 00:10:21.705
Who's going to feed the
civilians and soldiers?

113
00:10:22.039 --> 00:10:24.416
Don't ask me. Professor.

114
00:10:24.625 --> 00:10:26.502
This is insane!

115
00:10:44.186 --> 00:10:46.230
Ah. Professor!

116
00:10:46.730 --> 00:10:51.068
I won't let my staff be evacuated!
Is that so?

117
00:10:51.235 --> 00:10:53.654
The food supply to Berlin will collapse!

118
00:10:54.196 --> 00:10:57.116
A good soldier always finds food!
Sure!

119
00:10:57.366 --> 00:11:02.329
And when fighting begins. who will
he take food from? Civilians!

120
00:11:02.621 --> 00:11:05.457
I cannot permit it!
The Führer orders!

121
00:11:07.751 --> 00:11:10.754
As the department head. I
answer to the SS and to Himmler!

122
00:11:11.088 --> 00:11:15.759
But as a doctor I belong to the
Wehrmacht and we are still here!

123
00:11:16.135 --> 00:11:18.470
Please bear that in mind!

124
00:11:23.267 --> 00:11:27.271
The professor can stay in Berlin!
Give him an authorized permit!

125
00:11:30.566 --> 00:11:32.109
Move out!

126
00:11:45.414 --> 00:11:48.167
Everything for Germany.
Heil. my Führer!

127
00:11:49.710 --> 00:11:53.130
My Führer. I...
Heil. my Führer!

128
00:11:53.714 --> 00:11:56.634
They can hardly wait to get away.

129
00:11:57.134 --> 00:11:59.303
I hate those two-faced sods
who say "Sieg Heil"...

130
00:11:59.511 --> 00:12:03.432
but behind their backs say.
"Go fu... screw yourselves".

131
00:12:07.186 --> 00:12:08.604
My Führer...

132
00:12:08.729 --> 00:12:12.650
I beg you to leave Berlin.
It's not too late.

133
00:12:12.733 --> 00:12:15.027
Too late?

134
00:12:15.819 --> 00:12:18.322
Come here. Hewel.

135
00:12:19.281 --> 00:12:23.327
Hewel. you also feel we should
get in touch with the Allies...

136
00:12:23.744 --> 00:12:25.829
and use politics.

137
00:12:26.163 --> 00:12:29.416
Yes. indeed.
We should use politics.

138
00:12:29.541 --> 00:12:33.671
Politics? No more politics!

139
00:12:34.088 --> 00:12:37.174
I'm sick of politics!

140
00:12:37.758 --> 00:12:41.679
When I'm dead. you'll have
enough politics to deal with!

141
00:12:41.762 --> 00:12:46.183
My Führer...
It's okay. my dear Himmler.

142
00:12:46.767 --> 00:12:49.770
My loyal Heinrich.

143
00:12:50.479 --> 00:12:54.358
It's okay. Go now.

144
00:13:14.003 --> 00:13:16.338
Between us. I'd say he's had it.
Yeah?

145
00:13:16.463 --> 00:13:20.384
What do you expect from a teetotal.
non-smoking vegetarian?

146
00:13:20.592 --> 00:13:24.471
Be serious. I'll have to take
it into my own hands.

147
00:13:25.014 --> 00:13:27.599
Berlin will fall in the next few days.

148
00:13:27.808 --> 00:13:32.604
Once the Führer is dead.
who will the Allies negotiate with?

149
00:13:33.147 --> 00:13:36.108
What makes you so sure
they'll negotiate?

150
00:13:36.275 --> 00:13:40.029
They need the Nazi state and my
SS to keep order after the war.

151
00:13:40.154 --> 00:13:43.532
Give me an hour with
Eisenhower and he'll agree.

152
00:13:43.741 --> 00:13:48.245
We're already in touch.
Be careful. that's treason.

153
00:13:48.370 --> 00:13:51.040
Fegelein. I have other worries.

154
00:13:51.373 --> 00:13:56.378
Should I give Eisenhower the
Nazi salute or shake his hand?

155
00:14:02.801 --> 00:14:04.053
Well. well...

156
00:14:07.431 --> 00:14:09.266
the later it gets. the nicer the guests.

157
00:14:09.433 --> 00:14:14.396
Gentlemen. are you leaving already?
I wanted to talk to you.

158
00:14:15.439 --> 00:14:20.402
The Führer orders to destroy all...
I really must go.

159
00:14:20.861 --> 00:14:23.447
Drop in to visit me at
Hohenlychen sometime.

160
00:14:25.824 --> 00:14:31.080
My staff and I are heading north
to support the battle for Berlin.

161
00:14:41.090 --> 00:14:42.174
<i>So. Speer...</i>

162
00:14:42.341 --> 00:14:46.303
the bombing raids on our cities
have a positive side too.

163
00:14:46.595 --> 00:14:51.809
It's much easier to remove debris
than to tear everything down.

164
00:14:53.102 --> 00:14:56.980
Once we win the war. reconstruction
will be completed very quickly.

165
00:14:58.440 --> 00:15:03.987
How many thousands of hours have we
spent on these magnificent models?

166
00:15:05.781 --> 00:15:09.326
You're a true genius. Speer.

167
00:15:10.119 --> 00:15:11.245
Yes. you are.

168
00:15:11.495 --> 00:15:15.707
Only you and I realize that
a Third Reich isn't possible...

169
00:15:16.041 --> 00:15:18.585
if it only consists of department
stores and factories...

170
00:15:19.128 --> 00:15:22.005
skyscrapers and hotels.

171
00:15:22.256 --> 00:15:26.343
This Third Reich will be a treasure
house of art and culture...

172
00:15:26.593 --> 00:15:29.721
that will survive the millennia.

173
00:15:30.597 --> 00:15:35.227
We see before us the ancient
cities. the Acropolis...

174
00:15:35.394 --> 00:15:38.814
we see medieval cities
with their cathedrals...

175
00:15:39.148 --> 00:15:42.609
and we know that people
need something like this. a center.

176
00:15:45.612 --> 00:15:49.408
Yes. Speer...

177
00:15:50.492 --> 00:15:53.745
that was my vision...

178
00:15:54.663 --> 00:15:57.416
and it still is.

179
00:15:59.251 --> 00:16:05.048
My Führer. if you want to realize
this plan. you should leave Berlin.

180
00:16:10.554 --> 00:16:14.641
Say something. Eva.
He's the Führer.

181
00:16:15.559 --> 00:16:19.271
He knows what's right.
Please leave Berlin.

182
00:16:20.063 --> 00:16:22.399
The Russians have nearly cut us off.

183
00:16:22.566 --> 00:16:25.068
I can't do that. child.

184
00:16:25.277 --> 00:16:30.657
I'd feel like a Lama priest
spinning an empty prayer-wheel.

185
00:16:30.991 --> 00:16:36.330
I must force an outcome in Berlin
or face my downfall.

186
00:16:37.706 --> 00:16:40.209
Speer...

187
00:16:41.710 --> 00:16:44.338
What do you say?

188
00:16:44.796 --> 00:16:48.133
You must be on stage
when the curtain falls.

189
00:16:59.436 --> 00:17:01.563
Reload!

190
00:17:17.621 --> 00:17:19.748
Leave me alone!

191
00:17:20.499 --> 00:17:24.461
How old are you? 12? And you? 14?

192
00:17:24.628 --> 00:17:27.589
And you? Do you want to play war?
Go home. play another game!

193
00:17:27.756 --> 00:17:28.882
Who are you?

194
00:17:29.258 --> 00:17:32.219
What do you want?
My son... alive.

195
00:17:32.386 --> 00:17:35.639
You should be proud of him.
He destroyed two tanks today.

196
00:17:36.014 --> 00:17:38.267
The Führer is giving him a medal.

197
00:17:39.643 --> 00:17:42.646
You're young.
On which front did you fight?

198
00:17:43.647 --> 00:17:45.232
I haven't had the honor yet.

199
00:17:45.774 --> 00:17:50.737
You're lucky you haven't seen a
battle yet. Send the children home.

200
00:17:51.071 --> 00:17:53.657
We will fight to the very last man.

201
00:17:54.116 --> 00:17:57.536
What are you defending?
This is nothing but a trap.

202
00:17:57.786 --> 00:18:01.665
The Russians will attack from
both sides. so there's no escape.

203
00:18:02.165 --> 00:18:04.175
We'll shoot back at them!
With what?

204
00:18:04.751 --> 00:18:07.087
We're using flak as artillery.

205
00:18:07.254 --> 00:18:11.258
The Russians are coming. several
armies with tanks. heavy artillery.

206
00:18:11.508 --> 00:18:15.637
You really believe you can hold off
their assault for even 5 minutes?

207
00:18:16.138 --> 00:18:19.141
We made our pledge to the Führer.

208
00:18:19.308 --> 00:18:22.811
Don't you understand?
We've lost the war! It's over!

209
00:18:23.103 --> 00:18:24.688
Coward!

210
00:18:28.692 --> 00:18:31.695
Get outta here! Now!

211
00:18:32.112 --> 00:18:36.658
When the Russians come and
you're still here. you'll all die!

212
00:18:40.120 --> 00:18:43.457
I may be repeating myself.
but the 9th Army must retreat.

213
00:18:43.665 --> 00:18:48.837
Otherwise. it will be wiped out.
The 9th Army will not retreat!

214
00:18:49.129 --> 00:18:51.673
Tell Busse to fight where he stands.

215
00:18:52.090 --> 00:18:54.718
In that case. the 9th Army is lost.

216
00:18:55.093 --> 00:18:58.304
We will drive back
the Soviet units...

217
00:18:58.305 --> 00:19:01.141
in the north and east...

218
00:19:01.308 --> 00:19:05.354
with a relentless and almighty assault.

219
00:19:06.063 --> 00:19:07.856
With which units?

220
00:19:08.148 --> 00:19:12.736
Steiner's division will attack from
the north and unite with the 9th.

221
00:19:14.738 --> 00:19:17.699
The 9th Army is unable to move north.

222
00:19:17.991 --> 00:19:20.494
The enemy outnumbers us 10 to 1.

223
00:19:20.702 --> 00:19:23.997
Have Wenck support them
with the 12th Army.

224
00:19:24.373 --> 00:19:27.209
But the 12th Army is marching
west. to the Elbe.

225
00:19:27.459 --> 00:19:29.711
Then tell them to turn around!

226
00:19:30.087 --> 00:19:35.592
That'd expose the Western front.
Are you questioning my orders?

227
00:19:35.759 --> 00:19:39.346
I believe I've made
myself perfectly clear!

228
00:19:40.180 --> 00:19:44.601
The western Allies will realize that
only we can hold off the Bolsheviks.

229
00:19:44.768 --> 00:19:47.354
We're the last bulwark
against the Asian hordes.

230
00:19:47.604 --> 00:19:51.483
We hold Berlin for a few more days;
we make a deal with the Americans.

231
00:20:10.752 --> 00:20:14.256
Ah. Mohnke. you're here.

232
00:20:14.423 --> 00:20:16.383
My Führer.

233
00:20:16.633 --> 00:20:19.386
I put "Clausewitz" into effect today.

234
00:20:19.553 --> 00:20:21.513
Berlin is now a front-line city.

235
00:20:21.638 --> 00:20:26.268
You're in charge of defending
the government district.

236
00:20:27.269 --> 00:20:31.189
If there's a battle in Berlin.
we'll fight to the last man.

237
00:20:31.273 --> 00:20:35.402
But there are over 3 millions civilians.
They must be evacuated.

238
00:20:37.446 --> 00:20:40.574
I appreciate your concern. Mohnke.

239
00:20:41.408 --> 00:20:44.244
But we have to be cold-blooded.

240
00:20:44.411 --> 00:20:47.831
We can't worry about these
so-called civilians now!

241
00:20:49.332 --> 00:20:53.587
With all due respect. what will
become of the women and children...

242
00:20:53.837 --> 00:20:55.714
the thousands of wounded and the elderly?

243
00:20:57.549 --> 00:21:01.303
In a war like this
there are no civilians.

244
00:21:01.470 --> 00:21:04.598
The Führer has lost
all sense of reality.

245
00:21:04.806 --> 00:21:07.851
He moves divisions that
only exist on his map.

246
00:21:08.226 --> 00:21:11.229
Steiner's scattered unit
can hardly defend itself.

247
00:21:11.354 --> 00:21:14.691
He wants it to attack. It's insane!
Tell him yourself.

248
00:21:14.858 --> 00:21:19.112
He wouldn't listen. You know that.
Something has to be done.

249
00:21:19.237 --> 00:21:21.698
Are you crazy? He'd kick us out
like Rundstedt and Guderian.

250
00:21:22.073 --> 00:21:23.700
So what?

251
00:21:24.701 --> 00:21:29.122
We're soldiers! We pledged
our allegiance to the Führer!

252
00:21:29.289 --> 00:21:31.249
Should that prevent us from thinking?

253
00:21:31.458 --> 00:21:35.295
Look who's talking! An opportunist!
A ruthless careerist!

254
00:21:35.462 --> 00:21:37.380
Pardon?

255
00:22:02.113 --> 00:22:04.982
Where were you?
None of your damned business!

256
00:22:12.749 --> 00:22:17.295
My Fuhrer. Berlin Hitler Youth's
most successful tank hunters.

257
00:22:26.388 --> 00:22:29.140
I'm proud of you all.

258
00:22:30.809 --> 00:22:35.772
My Führer. this boy alone destroyed
two tanks with a bazooka.

259
00:22:36.147 --> 00:22:38.066
His name is Peter Kranz.

260
00:22:38.525 --> 00:22:41.570
So your name is Peter.

261
00:22:42.529 --> 00:22:46.658
I wish my generals
had your courage.

262
00:22:56.334 --> 00:22:59.212
Fine. fine.

263
00:23:03.425 --> 00:23:06.428
History will take note of you.

264
00:23:06.595 --> 00:23:11.349
And when Germania rises
up from these ruins...

265
00:23:11.600 --> 00:23:14.561
you'll be the heroes.

266
00:23:15.437 --> 00:23:18.690
Heil to you!

267
00:23:47.135 --> 00:23:51.389
I don't know. this gives me the
creeps. I prefer bombing raids.

268
00:23:52.098 --> 00:23:53.475
What will happen to us?

269
00:23:53.850 --> 00:23:57.479
Yesterday. he told me
it was all right if I left.

270
00:23:57.729 --> 00:24:02.400
Everyone's deserting him.
We can't just get up and leave.

271
00:24:02.609 --> 00:24:04.611
I can't either.

272
00:24:10.283 --> 00:24:13.286
I've no idea where I should go.

273
00:24:13.453 --> 00:24:17.791
My parents and friends
back home warned me.

274
00:24:18.166 --> 00:24:21.544
They told me not to get
involved with the Nazis.

275
00:24:21.753 --> 00:24:25.173
Should I go back and say.
"I'm home? I made a mistake

276
00:24:25.382 --> 00:24:27.634
When things got bad.
I realized my mistake".

277
00:24:29.302 --> 00:24:33.056
Life will go on somehow.

278
00:24:40.563 --> 00:24:44.067
What do you think. Colonel?
We should go.

279
00:24:46.528 --> 00:24:48.405
Where to?

280
00:24:48.530 --> 00:24:51.658
I don't know.
Someplace where we're needed.

281
00:25:03.670 --> 00:25:07.507
Come upstairs. everyone!
We're going to have a party!

282
00:25:07.674 --> 00:25:09.342
Come on!

283
00:25:12.095 --> 00:25:14.097
Come on. kids!

284
00:25:21.229 --> 00:25:23.356
I want us to have some fun today.

285
00:25:29.362 --> 00:25:33.700
No matter where the enemy goes. he
has to find nothing but wasteland.

286
00:25:35.326 --> 00:25:39.247
That's the death sentence
for the German people.

287
00:25:39.456 --> 00:25:43.501
No electricity. no gas. no clean
water. no coal. no transportation.

288
00:25:43.626 --> 00:25:46.463
By destroying all our railways.
canals. clocks. ships. locomotives

289
00:25:46.588 --> 00:25:50.717
we would hurl Germany
back to the Middle Ages.

290
00:25:51.384 --> 00:25:55.096
You'd be robbing our people
of every chance to survive.

291
00:25:55.263 --> 00:26:00.101
If the war is lost. it's immaterial
if the people perish too.

292
00:26:00.268 --> 00:26:02.728
It is not necessary to consider

293
00:26:02.729 --> 00:26:06.775
the German people's survival needs.

294
00:26:07.025 --> 00:26:10.278
On the contrary. it is better to
destroy those things ourselves.

295
00:26:10.403 --> 00:26:12.614
They have proved
themselves too weak

296
00:26:12.781 --> 00:26:16.743
and it is a law of nature that
they will be exterminated.

297
00:26:17.660 --> 00:26:20.288
They are your people.
You are the Führer.

298
00:26:21.289 --> 00:26:25.794
The only ones who will survive
the battle are the inferior ones.

299
00:26:26.169 --> 00:26:28.671
Our best people have fallen already.

300
00:26:34.427 --> 00:26:36.179
Here you go.

301
00:26:36.387 --> 00:26:39.265
Oh. come on. you're
supposed to dance.

302
00:26:40.391 --> 00:26:43.770
Shall I have this dance. lady?
With pleasure.

303
00:27:08.795 --> 00:27:11.589
Excuse me.
Yes. of course.

304
00:27:12.048 --> 00:27:14.217
What's the matter?

305
00:27:18.596 --> 00:27:21.558
Convince him that we have
to leave Berlin. Eva!

306
00:27:25.812 --> 00:27:28.815
Or come with me.

307
00:27:32.610 --> 00:27:33.736
Eva!

308
00:27:36.489 --> 00:27:39.242
You're going to die.

309
00:27:58.845 --> 00:28:02.640
Put on the music!
I want to dance!

310
00:28:02.765 --> 00:28:05.143
DEUCE!

311
00:28:07.770 --> 00:28:10.690
Anything in particular?
Swing.

312
00:28:39.510 --> 00:28:41.638
Traudl

313
00:28:42.305 --> 00:28:44.682
Traudl

314
00:28:46.142 --> 00:28:49.145
It's all so unreal

315
00:28:49.312 --> 00:28:55.193
like a dream where you want
to wake up. but you can't.

316
00:28:55.443 --> 00:28:58.154
It keeps going on and on.

317
00:29:01.074 --> 00:29:05.328
Gerda. I feel sick.

318
00:29:40.321 --> 00:29:42.615
Come on!

319
00:29:42.782 --> 00:29:45.827
Come on!

320
00:29:58.339 --> 00:30:03.219
I haven't moved my command...

321
00:30:05.346 --> 00:30:08.725
I haven't moved my command post!

322
00:30:09.392 --> 00:30:12.228
To the west?

323
00:30:12.395 --> 00:30:15.398
I'm 1.000 meters from the enemy!
General!

324
00:30:28.661 --> 00:30:31.664
Hello? Hello!

325
00:30:36.002 --> 00:30:38.004
The report. General?

326
00:30:38.254 --> 00:30:41.507
I'm to be shot.
What? What for?

327
00:30:41.674 --> 00:30:46.637
They claim that I moved my command
post westward away from the enemy.

328
00:30:46.804 --> 00:30:49.432
Not a bad idea.

329
00:30:49.849 --> 00:30:52.268
Come with me.

330
00:31:07.575 --> 00:31:09.035
Schenck.
<i>Mohnke.</i>

331
00:31:09.327 --> 00:31:14.415
I'm at the chancellery bunker
defending the government district.

332
00:31:14.791 --> 00:31:16.584
<i>I need your help.</i>

333
00:31:16.709 --> 00:31:19.295
That's difficult. everyone's been evacuated.

334
00:31:19.462 --> 00:31:21.881
Everyone's gone except
me and my adjutant.

335
00:31:22.298 --> 00:31:24.342
You're a doctor?
Yes. Internist.

336
00:31:24.675 --> 00:31:28.846
Find a vehicle and bring us
all the morphine. penicillin...

337
00:31:29.097 --> 00:31:31.599
and first-aid supplies you can find!

338
00:31:32.809 --> 00:31:36.062
I'll see what I can do.
Thank you and hurry.

339
00:32:26.154 --> 00:32:28.281
I have to see the Führer.

340
00:32:29.615 --> 00:32:32.243
What for?
I'm to be shot.

341
00:32:36.414 --> 00:32:39.125
Wait here.

342
00:32:39.375 --> 00:32:41.544
Your guns. please.

343
00:32:47.550 --> 00:32:49.802
Not here.

344
00:32:52.680 --> 00:32:56.058
Guard post 2. Rogen

345
00:32:58.060 --> 00:33:00.396
General...

346
00:33:02.148 --> 00:33:04.400
Not you.

347
00:33:23.794 --> 00:33:26.797
Heil Hitler.
Heil Hitler.

348
00:33:27.048 --> 00:33:30.092
What's going on?
Why am I to be shot?

349
00:33:30.301 --> 00:33:35.056
You know the Führer has forbidden
any westward retreat.

350
00:33:35.181 --> 00:33:39.810
Officers who disobey are to be
arrested and shot on the spot.

351
00:33:40.228 --> 00:33:44.106
What do you mean? My units have
been in fierce battle for days!

352
00:33:44.315 --> 00:33:48.611
My command post is just one
kilometer from the front line.

353
00:33:49.195 --> 00:33:51.447
Go on.

354
00:33:51.739 --> 00:33:56.202
You see this. don't you?
Don't use that tone with me!

355
00:33:57.203 --> 00:34:00.206
Now do what you have to do!

356
00:34:00.873 --> 00:34:05.253
I think you should explain it to
the Fuhrer yourself. Come along.

357
00:34:20.268 --> 00:34:23.103
I can't let you through.
I'm here on orders from Mohnke.

358
00:34:24.480 --> 00:34:27.692
We need first-aid material
from the military hospital.

359
00:34:27.858 --> 00:34:31.070
It's empty. They all left.

360
00:34:31.195 --> 00:34:33.698
And the wounded?
How should I know?

361
00:34:34.448 --> 00:34:35.608
I'll have a look.
Colonel!

362
00:34:35.616 --> 00:34:39.078
Stay here!
Careful you don't get killed.

363
00:34:39.245 --> 00:34:41.497
There are Russians everywhere.

364
00:34:41.706 --> 00:34:43.374
See that?

365
00:34:43.499 --> 00:34:46.252
It's the end of the Reich.
That's Russki territory!

366
00:34:58.472 --> 00:35:00.725
May I?

367
00:35:06.272 --> 00:35:11.068
He's so damn stubborn.
Why didn't he let me do it?

368
00:35:35.259 --> 00:35:37.511
Hello?

369
00:36:11.837 --> 00:36:15.800
I should be with my troops.
Are you sure the Führer needs me?

370
00:36:16.133 --> 00:36:19.345
Drink up!
The Führer orders!

371
00:36:19.553 --> 00:36:25.309
You really impressed the Führer.
You don't think Steiner will attack?

372
00:36:25.518 --> 00:36:27.728
I doubt that Steiner's units
are able to attack...

373
00:36:28.062 --> 00:36:31.816
but why am I telling you this?
You know better than I do.

374
00:36:32.274 --> 00:36:35.820
If Steiner doesn't attack.
Berlin will be lost.

375
00:36:45.371 --> 00:36:48.374
Congratulations. your report
really impressed the Führer.

376
00:36:48.582 --> 00:36:52.378
He has appointed you commander
of Berlin's defense.

377
00:36:53.087 --> 00:36:57.591
I'd rather have been shot
than have this honor.

378
00:37:22.366 --> 00:37:24.452
Tank alarm!

379
00:37:25.619 --> 00:37:30.624
Stay calm. They're too far
away to do anything.

380
00:37:47.308 --> 00:37:49.727
Out of the way. please. ladies.

381
00:38:19.173 --> 00:38:22.676
Is that German artillery out there?
I'm afraid not.

382
00:38:23.093 --> 00:38:26.472
But Steiner's attack should
be underway by now!

383
00:38:28.682 --> 00:38:31.268
You have to leave.
There isn't much time.

384
00:38:31.477 --> 00:38:37.149
But the Führer believes Steiner's
attack will improve the situation.

385
00:38:37.274 --> 00:38:40.694
I heard him say that Steiner's
assault will turn things around.

386
00:38:41.111 --> 00:38:44.490
All the Führer advisors
know that's absurd!

387
00:38:45.324 --> 00:38:47.660
I'd not be surprised
if he thinks so too.

388
00:38:47.785 --> 00:38:50.454
Why would he deceive us?

389
00:38:50.704 --> 00:38:52.456
What does he have to lose?

390
00:38:54.208 --> 00:38:55.501
I don't believe a word of it!

391
00:38:56.252 --> 00:38:59.338
The enemy has broken
through along a wide front.

392
00:38:59.505 --> 00:39:03.259
They've taken Zossen to the south
and are advancing to Stahnsdorf.

393
00:39:03.509 --> 00:39:07.304
They're on the northern outskirts
between Frohnau and Pankow.

394
00:39:07.638 --> 00:39:12.184
They've reached Lichtenberg.
Mahlsdorf. Karlshorst to the east.

395
00:39:13.018 --> 00:39:16.689
Steiner's assault will
bring it under control.

396
00:39:20.234 --> 00:39:22.278
My Führer...

397
00:39:23.320 --> 00:39:25.197
Steiner...

398
00:39:26.699 --> 00:39:29.201
Steiner couldn't mobilize enough men.

399
00:39:29.743 --> 00:39:32.246
He wasn't able to carry out his assault.

400
00:39:48.429 --> 00:39:54.226
These men will stay here:
Keitel. Jodl. Krebs and Burgdorf.

401
00:40:08.699 --> 00:40:10.701
That was an order!

402
00:40:10.826 --> 00:40:14.330
Steiner's assault was an order!

403
00:40:14.496 --> 00:40:20.044
Who do you think you are to dare
disobey an order that I give?

404
00:40:21.337 --> 00:40:27.051
The military has been lying to me.

405
00:40:27.259 --> 00:40:30.262
Everybody has been lying to me.
Even the SS!

406
00:40:30.387 --> 00:40:36.060
Our generals are just a bunch
of contemptible. disloyal cowards.

407
00:40:36.268 --> 00:40:38.520
I can't permit you to insult the soldiers...

408
00:40:38.646 --> 00:40:41.815
They are cowards. traitors and failures!

409
00:40:42.232 --> 00:40:44.360
My Führer. this is outrageous!

410
00:40:44.526 --> 00:40:48.364
Our generals are the scum
of the German people!

411
00:40:48.530 --> 00:40:51.241
Not a shred of honor!

412
00:40:51.492 --> 00:40:56.288
They call themselves generals!
Years at military academy

413
00:40:56.455 --> 00:40:59.333
just to learn how to
hold a knife and fork!

414
00:41:00.084 --> 00:41:03.629
For years. the military
has hindered my plans!

415
00:41:04.630 --> 00:41:09.635
They've put every kind
of obstacle in my way!

416
00:41:09.843 --> 00:41:13.263
What I should have done

417
00:41:13.430 --> 00:41:18.310
is liquidate all the high-ranking
officers. as Stalin did!

418
00:41:22.815 --> 00:41:25.609
I never attended an academy

419
00:41:26.110 --> 00:41:29.779
and yet I have conquered Europe

420
00:41:29.780 --> 00:41:32.491
all by myself!

421
00:41:36.704 --> 00:41:38.414
Traitors!

422
00:41:38.580 --> 00:41:41.083
I've been betrayed and deceived

423
00:41:41.107 --> 00:41:43.307
from the very beginning!

424
00:41:44.420 --> 00:41:49.550
What a monstrous betrayal
of the German people.

425
00:41:49.717 --> 00:41:53.637
But all those traitors will pay.
They'll pay with their own blood.

426
00:41:55.806 --> 00:41:59.727
They shall drown in their own blood!

427
00:42:00.519 --> 00:42:03.230
Gerda. please calm yourself.

428
00:42:10.154 --> 00:42:13.991
My orders have fallen
on deaf ears.

429
00:42:14.700 --> 00:42:20.122
Under these circumstances.
I am no longer able to lead.

430
00:42:21.206 --> 00:42:23.417
It's over.

431
00:42:27.254 --> 00:42:30.632
The war is lost.

432
00:42:36.430 --> 00:42:42.186
But if you believe I'll leave Berlin.
you are seriously mistaken.

433
00:42:42.394 --> 00:42:45.564
I'd rather blow my brains out.

434
00:42:49.568 --> 00:42:52.196
Do whatever you like.

435
00:43:12.591 --> 00:43:16.220
The Führer didn't really
mean he'd shoot himself.

436
00:43:16.428 --> 00:43:19.640
<i>Frau</i> Junge and <i>Frau</i> Christian...

437
00:43:22.559 --> 00:43:27.481
get changed. A plane is leaving
in an hour. It will take you south.

438
00:43:28.774 --> 00:43:31.401
Everything is lost.

439
00:43:31.610 --> 00:43:34.154
hopelessly lost.

440
00:43:37.199 --> 00:43:41.453
You know I'll stay with you.
I won't let you send me away.

441
00:43:53.465 --> 00:43:55.801
I'm staying too!

442
00:44:19.783 --> 00:44:21.660
What now?

443
00:44:21.785 --> 00:44:23.662
It's time to end this spectacle.

444
00:44:24.037 --> 00:44:29.209
What? You want to give up?
That's unthinkable.

445
00:44:29.376 --> 00:44:33.255
The Führer said we won't surrender.
We won't repeat November 1918.

446
00:44:33.380 --> 00:44:36.300
Never!
You heard. He'll no longer lead us.

447
00:44:36.758 --> 00:44:41.597
He said. "Do whatever you want".
The Führer is the Führer!

448
00:44:42.598 --> 00:44:45.309
He'll pull himself together.

449
00:44:45.517 --> 00:44:48.604
Great.
And what happens then?

450
00:44:51.315 --> 00:44:54.375
We can never surrender.
The Führer would never approve.

451
00:44:54.735 --> 00:44:58.071
We swore to obey his will.
Nothing but empty phrases!

452
00:44:58.322 --> 00:45:01.325
We have to do something
before it's too late.

453
00:45:01.491 --> 00:45:03.619
You want to save your own skin.
Stop it!

454
00:45:13.629 --> 00:45:15.172
Damn it!

455
00:45:19.635 --> 00:45:23.597
We'll never get out alive.
It's all over.

456
00:45:24.514 --> 00:45:25.557
Just wait.

457
00:45:25.807 --> 00:45:29.353
But the Führer is uncertain.
What if he kills himself?

458
00:45:30.354 --> 00:45:34.775
Günsche said there's a tunnel under
the Russian lines to the Yanks.

459
00:45:35.108 --> 00:45:41.114
Why'd you say you'd stay with him?
I don't know... honestly.

460
00:45:44.701 --> 00:45:48.029
They've stopped. Come on.
Let's go for a walk.

461
00:46:29.162 --> 00:46:30.706
Traudl...

462
00:46:30.998 --> 00:46:32.416
Look.

463
00:46:54.813 --> 00:46:58.233
Hey. girls. I need a cigarette.

464
00:47:15.834 --> 00:47:18.420
Let's go back down again.

465
00:47:48.492 --> 00:47:50.410
Where did they come from?

466
00:47:50.535 --> 00:47:52.687
New Volkssturm recruits!
Assigned this afternoon!

467
00:47:52.788 --> 00:47:56.166
Tell them to get out
of the line of fire!

468
00:47:59.044 --> 00:48:03.990
These recruits are under
Dr. Goebbels' command!

469
00:48:06.510 --> 00:48:11.014
I want them out of there right away!

470
00:48:11.223 --> 00:48:12.766
I'll answer for it.

471
00:48:24.236 --> 00:48:27.531
I'm not sure it's the right way.
Oh. splendid.

472
00:48:29.032 --> 00:48:31.284
Stop! Lights out!

473
00:48:31.451 --> 00:48:35.831
Stop. Don't move. Don't move.

474
00:48:36.289 --> 00:48:38.375
Lucky! Germans.

475
00:48:41.545 --> 00:48:44.089
Help! They want to kill us!

476
00:48:44.548 --> 00:48:47.509
What's going on here?
They're MPs.

477
00:48:47.717 --> 00:48:49.553
I don't believe it!

478
00:48:59.563 --> 00:49:03.400
Stop it! Let those men go!

479
00:49:03.567 --> 00:49:06.736
What's going on here?
It's none of your business!

480
00:49:07.028 --> 00:49:09.614
We found these deserters
in their homes.

481
00:49:10.073 --> 00:49:12.117
They'll be shot. like every traitor.

482
00:49:12.325 --> 00:49:15.834
They're old men. civilians.
You can't do that!

483
00:49:16.371 --> 00:49:18.081
No?

484
00:49:20.584 --> 00:49:23.587
Who's going to stop me? You?

485
00:49:25.130 --> 00:49:27.382
That's enough.

486
00:49:41.605 --> 00:49:43.273
Move out!

487
00:51:26.751 --> 00:51:29.087
Here's a doctor.

488
00:51:36.177 --> 00:51:39.139
Can you operate?
Not really.

489
00:51:41.725 --> 00:51:44.477
Tell Ilse that the children
can't take too many toys.

490
00:51:44.728 --> 00:51:46.313
One toy per child.

491
00:51:46.521 --> 00:51:51.526
And no unnecessary nightclothes.
Minister Goebbels...

492
00:51:51.735 --> 00:51:56.740
My wife and children are coming.
Please take care of them.

493
00:51:56.764 --> 00:51:57.414
Thank you.

494
00:51:57.415 --> 00:52:00.460
Brigadeführer. what can I do for you?

495
00:52:00.702 --> 00:52:04.205
The Russians are mowing down
your Volkssturm recruits.

496
00:52:04.331 --> 00:52:07.042
They lack experience
and suitable weapons.

497
00:52:07.292 --> 00:52:12.505
That is compensated for by their
fervent belief in the final victory.

498
00:52:13.298 --> 00:52:17.427
If you can't arm these
men. they can't fight.

499
00:52:17.552 --> 00:52:19.721
They are dying in vain.

500
00:52:20.138 --> 00:52:22.766
I feel no sympathy.

501
00:52:24.351 --> 00:52:29.522
I repeat. I feel no sympathy!
The German people chose their fate.

502
00:52:30.607 --> 00:52:33.151
That may surprise some people.

503
00:52:33.276 --> 00:52:36.571
Don't fool yourself.
We didn't force the German people.

504
00:52:37.155 --> 00:52:42.285
They gave us the mandate. And now
their little throats are being cut.

505
00:52:54.798 --> 00:52:55.907
Yes?

506
00:52:58.259 --> 00:52:59.386
<i>Hello?</i>

507
00:52:59.552 --> 00:53:01.262
Eva. you have to leave the Führer.

508
00:53:01.471 --> 00:53:03.139
Hermann!
<i>Don't be stupid.</i>

509
00:53:03.306 --> 00:53:04.857
It's a matter of life and death.

510
00:53:05.141 --> 00:53:07.519
How can you say such a thing?
Where are you?

511
00:53:08.186 --> 00:53:10.563
I've decided not to die in Berlin.

512
00:53:11.314 --> 00:53:13.608
Hermann. does my sister
know where you are?

513
00:53:14.150 --> 00:53:16.528
I have to call you back.

514
00:53:18.196 --> 00:53:21.116
Hi there. kids.
Your room's on the right.

515
00:53:22.826 --> 00:53:24.828
Wait for me.

516
00:53:26.079 --> 00:53:29.374
Hello. Frau Goebbels.
Nice to see you. Frau Junge.

517
00:53:41.136 --> 00:53:43.847
Come on now. get in line!

518
00:53:44.556 --> 00:53:46.599
Come here. Helga. Get in line.

519
00:53:48.059 --> 00:53:50.395
We'll put on our best clothes

520
00:53:50.603 --> 00:53:52.522
and then you can say
hello to Uncle Hitler.

521
00:53:52.647 --> 00:53:55.275
Yes! Yes! Yes!

522
00:53:56.526 --> 00:53:59.404
Remember your song?
Yes.

523
00:54:00.113 --> 00:54:04.117
<i>No land is more beautiful</i>

524
00:54:04.242 --> 00:54:10.123
<i>Far and wide</i>

525
00:54:10.373 --> 00:54:16.129
<i>Than the land</i>

526
00:54:16.337 --> 00:54:20.425
<i>We call our own</i>

527
00:54:20.633 --> 00:54:26.598
<i>Than the land</i>

528
00:54:26.806 --> 00:54:31.603
<i>We call our own</i>

529
00:54:38.109 --> 00:54:42.280
If you want to be certain.
shoot the gun into your mouth.

530
00:54:43.072 --> 00:54:45.450
Your skull will explode.

531
00:54:46.659 --> 00:54:50.413
You don't notice a thing.
You die immediately.

532
00:54:50.580 --> 00:54:53.500
I want to look nice when I'm dead.
I'll take poison.

533
00:54:53.666 --> 00:54:57.478
If I'm going to die heroically.
I don't want to feel any pain.

534
00:54:57.504 --> 00:54:59.339
That's a surefire way.

535
00:54:59.756 --> 00:55:04.319
It paralyzes the nerves
and the respiratory system.

536
00:55:04.385 --> 00:55:06.879
You die within seconds.

537
00:55:08.431 --> 00:55:11.509
Could I have one too?
Me too.

538
00:55:17.148 --> 00:55:22.036
Thank goodness. Himmler
left me well supplied.

539
00:55:39.546 --> 00:55:41.297
Thank you.

540
00:55:42.549 --> 00:55:48.471
I'm so sorry I can't give
you a better present.

541
00:55:55.478 --> 00:55:59.732
<i>"Berlin. April 23. 1945.</i>

542
00:56:03.236 --> 00:56:05.196
<i>My dearest sister.</i>

543
00:56:05.363 --> 00:56:08.575
<i>I'm so sorry I have
to write you this</i>

544
00:56:08.741 --> 00:56:10.492
<i>but there's nothing we can do.</i>

545
00:56:10.493 --> 00:56:13.454
<i>At any minute. it could all be over.</i>

546
00:56:14.247 --> 00:56:16.874
<i>You should know that
Hermann isn't here.</i>

547
00:56:17.750 --> 00:56:21.212
<i>But I truly believe you'll
see him again.</i>

548
00:56:22.005 --> 00:56:27.385
<i>I'm sure he'll continue the fight
in Bavaria for a certain time.</i>

549
00:56:27.510 --> 00:56:31.514
<i>The Führer has lost all belief
in a favorable outcome."</i>

550
00:56:33.182 --> 00:56:36.769
<i>"My beloved son. I don't know
if this letter will reach you.</i>

551
00:56:37.103 --> 00:56:39.229
<i>Perhaps there is some human soul</i>

552
00:56:39.230 --> 00:56:42.233
<i>who will pass on my
final words to you.</i>

553
00:56:42.692 --> 00:56:46.404
<i>I've stayed with Papa
against his will.</i>

554
00:56:46.529 --> 00:56:50.491
<i>Last Sunday. the Führer
wanted to help me leave.</i>

555
00:56:50.617 --> 00:56:53.536
<i>You know your mother well.
We have the same blood.</i>

556
00:56:53.703 --> 00:56:58.416
<i>I had no second thoughts.
Our magnificent idea has died</i>

557
00:56:58.583 --> 00:57:01.335
<i>along with every beautiful. noble</i>

558
00:57:01.336 --> 00:57:03.421
<i>admirable. good thing I ever known.</i>

559
00:57:03.588 --> 00:57:06.716
<i>The world after the Führer? death
and after National Socialism</i>

560
00:57:07.050 --> 00:57:11.471
<i>is no longer worth living in.
That's why the children are here.</i>

561
00:57:11.638 --> 00:57:14.098
<i>They are too good for what will come.</i>

562
00:57:14.307 --> 00:57:20.271
<i>Merciful God will understand me
for giving them redemption."</i>

563
00:57:26.736 --> 00:57:28.487
<i>"I'll wear the golden bracelet</i>

564
00:57:28.488 --> 00:57:31.074
<i>with the green stone
until the very end.</i>

565
00:57:31.783 --> 00:57:34.619
<i>Then it may be taken from me.
and you shall wear it</i>

566
00:57:35.119 --> 00:57:38.039
<i>just as I have always worn it.</i>

567
00:57:38.373 --> 00:57:42.293
<i>I'm afraid I sent my diamond
watch to the jeweler's.</i>

568
00:57:42.502 --> 00:57:44.170
<i>I wrote the address at the bottom.</i>

569
00:57:44.796 --> 00:57:47.340
<i>If you're lucky.
you can get it back.</i>

570
00:57:47.507 --> 00:57:49.801
<i>I want you to have it.</i>

571
00:57:50.843 --> 00:57:53.637
<i>You'll also get the diamond bracelet</i>

572
00:57:53.638 --> 00:57:55.555
<i>and the topaz pendant</i>

573
00:57:55.556 --> 00:57:58.267
<i>which the Führer gave me
for my birthday.</i>

574
00:57:59.477 --> 00:58:03.064
<i>The bill I'm including for
Heise & Co. hasn't been paid yet.</i>

575
00:58:03.314 --> 00:58:05.440
<i>You might receive other bills</i>

576
00:58:05.441 --> 00:58:09.362
<i>but not for more than
1.500 Reichsmarks.</i>

577
00:58:10.822 --> 00:58:14.408
<i>Please burn all private
and business letters</i>

578
00:58:14.409 --> 00:58:17.328
<i>to the Führer at once.</i>

579
00:58:19.122 --> 00:58:22.375
<i>I'm also sending you
food and cigarettes.</i>

580
00:58:22.542 --> 00:58:26.087
<i>Please give Lindners and Kargels
some of the coffee.</i>

581
00:58:26.212 --> 00:58:29.716
<i>The cigarettes are for Mandi.
The tobacco is for Papa.</i>

582
00:58:30.133 --> 00:58:31.676
<i>The chocolate is for Mom.</i>

583
00:58:31.884 --> 00:58:36.723
<i>That's all I can tell you.
It's enough for now.</i>

584
00:58:38.057 --> 00:58:41.686
<i>I wish you the best of luck.
my dearest sister.</i>

585
00:58:42.061 --> 00:58:43.312
<i>And remember.</i>

586
00:58:43.438 --> 00:58:45.648
<i>I'm sure you'll see Hermann again.</i>

587
00:58:45.982 --> 00:58:48.443
<i>Best regards and kisses.</i>

588
00:58:48.651 --> 00:58:50.403
<i>I remain</i>

589
00:58:50.528 --> 00:58:52.822
<i>your sister."</i>

590
00:59:43.664 --> 00:59:45.583
Inge!

591
00:59:46.459 --> 00:59:48.461
Inge!

592
01:00:35.550 --> 01:00:40.221
Listen. Keitel. I want
you to leave tonight.

593
01:00:40.513 --> 01:00:45.101
Make your way to Dönitz.
Help him organize everything.

594
01:00:45.268 --> 01:00:48.437
We have to get things moving again.

595
01:00:49.730 --> 01:00:52.066
I don't understand.

596
01:00:52.275 --> 01:00:56.279
It's a disaster.
We have no more oilfields.

597
01:00:56.487 --> 01:01:01.534
It's impossible to carry out
far-ranging operations.

598
01:01:02.326 --> 01:01:06.789
Once I've managed this situation.
we must recover the oilfields.

599
01:01:13.796 --> 01:01:15.840
Any more questions?

600
01:01:16.215 --> 01:01:20.803
No. my Führer.
Fine. Have a nice trip.

601
01:02:46.847 --> 01:02:52.561
"My Führer. following your
decision to stay in Berlin.

602
01:02:53.396 --> 01:02:55.480
do you approve me as Vice Chancellor

603
01:02:55.481 --> 01:02:57.149
to take charge of the entire Reich

604
01:02:57.650 --> 01:03:00.736
with the necessary power and authority?

605
01:03:01.112 --> 01:03:04.073
If I receive no answer by 10 p.m.

606
01:03:04.240 --> 01:03:07.076
I will assume that you
have been incapacitated.

607
01:03:07.201 --> 01:03:09.962
I will serve the well-being of
our people and Fatherland."

608
01:03:11.789 --> 01:03:14.792
He's betraying Germany and you!

609
01:03:15.167 --> 01:03:17.520
Göring's concern isn't unjustified.

610
01:03:17.628 --> 01:03:22.525
If our communication system breaks
down. which could happen any time.

611
01:03:22.633 --> 01:03:27.638
we'd be cut off from the world.
We could no longer pass on orders.

612
01:03:27.763 --> 01:03:30.808
I see it differently.
Göring wants to seize power.

613
01:03:31.183 --> 01:03:34.728
I never trusted that mob
he gathered at Obersalzberg.

614
01:03:34.729 --> 01:03:36.488
It stinks of a coup.

615
01:03:37.189 --> 01:03:41.610
That failure! That bloodsucker!

616
01:03:41.736 --> 01:03:44.805
A parvenu! A lazybones!

617
01:03:44.989 --> 01:03:50.161
How dare he declare me unable to act!

618
01:03:50.369 --> 01:03:52.455
Hello. Frau Junge.

619
01:03:52.663 --> 01:03:57.460
How did you reach Berlin?
Wasn't easy. I must see the Führer.

620
01:03:57.710 --> 01:04:01.422
I'd wait if I were you.
The air force...

621
01:04:01.839 --> 01:04:04.216
What did he do with it?

622
01:04:04.467 --> 01:04:07.678
That's reason enough to execute him!

623
01:04:07.803 --> 01:04:14.060
That morphine addict helped
to corrupt this country.

624
01:04:14.810 --> 01:04:16.437
And now this!

625
01:04:17.438 --> 01:04:20.483
He has betrayed me.

626
01:04:21.567 --> 01:04:24.820
Me!

627
01:04:31.243 --> 01:04:36.207
I want Goring to be deprived of
power and removed from office.

628
01:04:36.332 --> 01:04:39.543
If I don't survive this war.

629
01:04:39.752 --> 01:04:43.422
that man is to be executed at once.

630
01:04:45.007 --> 01:04:47.259
What about us?

631
01:04:47.760 --> 01:04:50.471
Is there any hope?

632
01:04:51.764 --> 01:04:55.267
Leave before it's too late.

633
01:04:55.434 --> 01:04:59.772
The Führer wants to stay here.
We can't leave him alone.

634
01:05:00.773 --> 01:05:06.278
For what awaits the Führer. he won't
need anyone. Least of all you.

635
01:05:06.487 --> 01:05:09.782
But Herr Goebbels and his wife
are staying. The children too.

636
01:05:20.042 --> 01:05:22.586
But the children...

637
01:05:25.798 --> 01:05:29.051
I'd always thought that...

638
01:05:29.468 --> 01:05:33.305
I thought there was some way out.

639
01:05:39.478 --> 01:05:41.355
Come in.

640
01:05:43.315 --> 01:05:46.235
Albert... hello.

641
01:05:57.079 --> 01:05:59.081
Fever?

642
01:05:59.498 --> 01:06:02.585
Albert. my heart can't take it.

643
01:06:05.004 --> 01:06:07.798
Why don't you take the children
and get out of here?

644
01:06:07.840 --> 01:06:10.676
But where to?

645
01:06:11.177 --> 01:06:16.348
I once told you. I can send
a barge to Schwanenwerder.

646
01:06:16.557 --> 01:06:20.561
It can be fixed up as a
hideout until it's all over.

647
01:06:20.686 --> 01:06:25.357
which won't be long.
I've thought it through carefully.

648
01:06:26.609 --> 01:06:32.114
I won't let the children grow up in
a world with no National Socialism.

649
01:06:35.117 --> 01:06:37.620
Think it over again. Magda.

650
01:06:38.204 --> 01:06:41.373
The children deserve a future.

651
01:06:44.210 --> 01:06:48.839
If the idea of National Socialism
dies. there is no future.

652
01:07:05.439 --> 01:07:08.651
I can't believe you really want this.

653
01:07:10.194 --> 01:07:12.196
Go.

654
01:07:43.686 --> 01:07:45.187
Come in.

655
01:07:49.692 --> 01:07:52.194
I knew you'd come.

656
01:07:52.403 --> 01:07:55.864
You're not one of those
who'd abandon the Führer.

657
01:07:58.450 --> 01:08:02.913
I've just come to say
goodbye to the Führer.

658
01:08:03.205 --> 01:08:05.148
I have to return to Hamburg tonight.

659
01:08:05.207 --> 01:08:07.710
Of course. Take a seat.

660
01:08:11.005 --> 01:08:14.633
Look. I brought some of the
furniture you designed for me.

661
01:08:14.758 --> 01:08:17.277
I just couldn't part with it.

662
01:08:17.303 --> 01:08:22.558
Come on. help yourself.
I bet you haven't eaten all day.

663
01:08:22.766 --> 01:08:25.102
You happen to be right.

664
01:08:26.145 --> 01:08:28.147
Thanks.

665
01:08:28.314 --> 01:08:31.108
It's so important that you came.

666
01:08:31.317 --> 01:08:34.194
It shows him you're on his side.

667
01:08:34.361 --> 01:08:36.822
Did he have his doubts?

668
01:08:37.740 --> 01:08:41.827
He's been wondering if you
were possibly against him.

669
01:08:42.119 --> 01:08:45.547
But I kept telling him you'd come.
And now you're here.

670
01:08:50.711 --> 01:08:54.773
It pleased him that you
advised him to stay in Berlin.

671
01:08:54.882 --> 01:08:57.793
I think it's the right choice too.

672
01:09:00.054 --> 01:09:01.513
You know what?

673
01:09:02.890 --> 01:09:06.352
It may be crazy. but...

674
01:09:06.727 --> 01:09:09.772
I'm really happy to be able to stay.

675
01:09:10.522 --> 01:09:13.400
And I'm not afraid.

676
01:09:21.533 --> 01:09:23.369
Yes?

677
01:09:38.050 --> 01:09:40.636
So you've come.

678
01:09:41.428 --> 01:09:43.806
My Führer...

679
01:09:44.098 --> 01:09:46.100
It's okay.

680
01:09:47.434 --> 01:09:50.187
Let's sit down.

681
01:10:06.829 --> 01:10:12.501
I had such big plans for the
Germans and for the world.

682
01:10:13.752 --> 01:10:18.841
No one understood me.
not even my oldest comrades.

683
01:10:23.178 --> 01:10:28.642
What huge opportunities we had.
The world was within reach.

684
01:10:32.229 --> 01:10:34.481
Too late.

685
01:10:40.195 --> 01:10:45.701
What I am proud of is that I
openly confronted the Jews

686
01:10:46.827 --> 01:10:51.290
and I cleansed the German
lands of Jewish poison.

687
01:10:56.044 --> 01:11:01.467
It isn't hard for me to go.
Just that one moment...

688
01:11:06.638 --> 01:11:10.267
and then eternal peace.

689
01:11:14.521 --> 01:11:17.733
Spare the German people. my Führer.

690
01:11:19.485 --> 01:11:23.489
If my own people fail this test.

691
01:11:23.614 --> 01:11:27.159
I will shed not one tear for them.

692
01:11:27.326 --> 01:11:29.536
They deserve nothing else.

693
01:11:29.703 --> 01:11:34.291
It's their own destiny.
They themselves are to blame.

694
01:11:40.672 --> 01:11:43.342
For months...

695
01:11:44.134 --> 01:11:47.387
I must tell you this. my Führer...

696
01:11:47.638 --> 01:11:52.226
For months I have not carried
out your orders of destruction.

697
01:11:53.560 --> 01:11:56.855
Documents exist which prove
that I not only ignored

698
01:11:57.356 --> 01:11:59.966
but even acted contrary to your orders.

699
01:12:05.405 --> 01:12:08.116
I had to tell you.

700
01:12:16.250 --> 01:12:19.845
My personal loyalty to you
never wavered throughout.

701
01:12:33.725 --> 01:12:37.104
So. you're leaving.

702
01:12:37.771 --> 01:12:41.567
Fine. Goodbye.

703
01:12:52.744 --> 01:12:55.289
I wish you all the best.

704
01:13:17.144 --> 01:13:21.148
So. gentlemen. eat your fill.

705
01:14:16.703 --> 01:14:18.538
Peter!

706
01:14:26.672 --> 01:14:30.717
Everything's okay. my boy.

707
01:14:46.274 --> 01:14:48.568
Fever.

708
01:14:50.195 --> 01:14:52.489
Yes. but he's alive.

709
01:15:16.304 --> 01:15:19.741
Courage and loyalty still exist.

710
01:15:20.976 --> 01:15:24.312
Lord von Greim and Frau Reitsch.

711
01:15:26.982 --> 01:15:31.419
I am pleased that you both
arrived uninjured. more or less.

712
01:15:31.737 --> 01:15:33.655
Be seated.

713
01:15:35.240 --> 01:15:38.560
We were under heavy fire
but were able to land in Gatow.

714
01:15:38.702 --> 01:15:42.289
The roads were impassable. so

715
01:15:42.581 --> 01:15:44.458
we got a plane.

716
01:15:44.624 --> 01:15:46.710
a Fieseler Storch and flew
over the Russian lines

717
01:15:46.835 --> 01:15:50.397
landing on the East-West axis.
a few hundred meters from here.

718
01:15:50.464 --> 01:15:53.725
Just before landing. we got
hit by Russian artillery.

719
01:15:54.593 --> 01:15:56.553
General von Greim.

720
01:15:56.720 --> 01:16:00.307
I appoint you Commander in
Chief of the Air Force

721
01:16:00.474 --> 01:16:03.226
and General Field Marshal.

722
01:16:03.810 --> 01:16:06.021
A great responsibility

723
01:16:06.229 --> 01:16:10.358
rests on your shoulders. You must
shake up the entire air force.

724
01:16:10.776 --> 01:16:14.237
Many mistakes have been made.
Be ruthless.

725
01:16:15.405 --> 01:16:19.451
Life never forgives weakness.

726
01:16:20.744 --> 01:16:23.789
This so-called humanity

727
01:16:24.456 --> 01:16:27.584
is just priests' drivel.

728
01:16:27.793 --> 01:16:33.215
Compassion is a primal sin.
Compassion for the weak

729
01:16:33.465 --> 01:16:35.801
is a betrayal of nature.

730
01:16:36.176 --> 01:16:41.640
The strongest can only be victorious
by eradicating the weak.

731
01:16:41.807 --> 01:16:45.352
I have always obeyed
this law of nature

732
01:16:46.144 --> 01:16:49.606
by never allowing myself
to feel compassion.

733
01:16:49.815 --> 01:16:52.851
I have ruthlessly suppressed
domestic opposition...

734
01:17:06.414 --> 01:17:08.416
Heil. my Führer.

735
01:17:11.503 --> 01:17:15.298
You have requested to leave Berlin?

736
01:17:16.299 --> 01:17:19.552
As you know. all medical units

737
01:17:19.553 --> 01:17:22.847
and staff under Himmler's authority

738
01:17:22.848 --> 01:17:24.516
have left Berlin.

739
01:17:24.683 --> 01:17:29.604
Himmler is a traitor. He will
receive the punishment he deserves.

740
01:17:29.771 --> 01:17:34.860
As an SS physician. I have
no more duties here.

741
01:17:35.193 --> 01:17:39.447
Your application to leave Berlin
is completely unacceptable.

742
01:17:40.699 --> 01:17:43.535
My... family...

743
01:17:44.286 --> 01:17:47.706
If the Russians find me here...
I have to leave!

744
01:17:48.206 --> 01:17:50.041
You did nothing wrong.

745
01:17:50.292 --> 01:17:53.335
Future generations will be thankful

746
01:17:53.336 --> 01:17:56.298
for the medical research you did.

747
01:17:56.464 --> 01:17:59.000
I'll take responsibility for it all.

748
01:18:04.639 --> 01:18:07.183
Let's discuss this another time.

749
01:18:21.573 --> 01:18:24.367
We can't find Gruppenführer Fegelein.

750
01:18:24.534 --> 01:18:29.331
He is not in the bunker.
What do you mean. can't find him?

751
01:18:29.581 --> 01:18:31.082
Then look for him!

752
01:18:31.625 --> 01:18:34.711
I want to see Fegelein at once!

753
01:18:35.086 --> 01:18:39.257
If he's gone AWOL.
it's desertion! Treason!

754
01:18:39.507 --> 01:18:44.971
Bring me Fegelein!
Fegelein! Fegelein!

755
01:18:55.857 --> 01:18:59.811
Dad. why are you wearing
your Sunday uniform?

756
01:19:02.364 --> 01:19:07.786
Ernst. is something wrong?
No. Thank you.

757
01:19:09.287 --> 01:19:12.457
Gitte is hungry too.

758
01:19:13.416 --> 01:19:18.046
Well. Ilse. now you have
to eat something too.

759
01:19:19.089 --> 01:19:22.175
Thank you.
You're welcome.

760
01:19:26.137 --> 01:19:28.348
Thank you.

761
01:20:21.443 --> 01:20:25.238
What's going on?
You're under arrest.

762
01:20:26.031 --> 01:20:27.741
What?
For desertion.

763
01:20:28.158 --> 01:20:30.744
Get dressed.
You must come with us.

764
01:20:31.077 --> 01:20:32.620
Kiss my ass!

765
01:20:35.749 --> 01:20:37.083
Come with us.

766
01:20:37.625 --> 01:20:40.670
Let go. you bastard!
You got no right!

767
01:20:43.048 --> 01:20:46.176
Please don't let them kill Hermann.

768
01:20:46.384 --> 01:20:49.103
He wanted to flee.
It's beyond doubt.

769
01:20:49.804 --> 01:20:52.006
So what?
It's all over anyway.

770
01:20:52.098 --> 01:20:57.145
Think of my poor sister.
She's pregnant!

771
01:20:57.604 --> 01:21:01.875
He collaborated with Himmler.
He's a traitor.

772
01:21:03.777 --> 01:21:06.454
There is no compassion for traitors.

773
01:21:06.529 --> 01:21:09.783
There is no mercy for traitors.

774
01:21:11.076 --> 01:21:15.121
He'll be court-martialed and shot.

775
01:21:15.288 --> 01:21:18.541
What good is that now?

776
01:21:19.334 --> 01:21:22.337
It is my will!

777
01:21:34.557 --> 01:21:36.650
You're the Führer.

778
01:21:39.354 --> 01:21:41.064
Go ahead.

779
01:21:41.189 --> 01:21:43.608
The Russians are breaking
through everywhere.

780
01:21:43.733 --> 01:21:47.320
There are no reserves left
and air support has stopped.

781
01:21:47.570 --> 01:21:50.073
There's no way to bring
in more ammunition.

782
01:21:54.828 --> 01:21:57.247
The Russians have reached
Weidendammer Bridge...

783
01:21:57.455 --> 01:22:01.084
Lustgarten to the east.
Potsdammerplatz to the south

784
01:22:01.251 --> 01:22:05.672
and Tiergarten to the west.
300-400 meters from the Chancellery.

785
01:22:05.797 --> 01:22:09.742
How long can you hold out?
One or two days at most.

786
01:22:10.135 --> 01:22:13.212
The government district too?
Yes. my Führer.

787
01:22:13.805 --> 01:22:17.108
My Führer. as a soldier.
I suggest we try

788
01:22:17.142 --> 01:22:21.621
to break through the encirclement.
During the fight for Berlin.

789
01:22:21.688 --> 01:22:26.476
We've already lost 15-20.000
of the younger officers.

790
01:22:26.484 --> 01:22:29.887
But that's what young men are for.

791
01:22:30.238 --> 01:22:34.075
Your suggestion is absurd! Insane!

792
01:22:34.200 --> 01:22:37.628
Think of the thousands of wounded.
We can't help them now.

793
01:22:37.745 --> 01:22:42.417
My Führer. the orders are ready.
I give you my word

794
01:22:42.625 --> 01:22:47.522
The Führer can't just disappear from
history like some infamous fugitive!

795
01:22:48.047 --> 01:22:51.759
Even if we got out successfully.

796
01:22:52.552 --> 01:22:56.281
I'd only be escaping one
trap to fall into another.

797
01:22:56.347 --> 01:23:01.744
I'd have to sleep in the open or in
a farmhouse or something similar

798
01:23:01.811 --> 01:23:04.706
and wait for the end to come.

799
01:23:05.190 --> 01:23:08.034
Wenck is approaching
with the 12th Army.

800
01:23:08.067 --> 01:23:11.296
He can unite with Busse's 9th Army

801
01:23:11.362 --> 01:23:15.942
and inflict a crushing blow on
the Russians to save us all.

802
01:23:16.034 --> 01:23:18.886
Wenck is a man of excellence.

803
01:23:19.245 --> 01:23:21.748
Telegraph Keitel.

804
01:23:23.374 --> 01:23:25.310
Report to me immediately:

805
01:23:25.335 --> 01:23:29.631
First. where are Wenck's front lines?

806
01:23:30.048 --> 01:23:33.318
Second. when are they attacking?

807
01:23:33.384 --> 01:23:36.237
Third. where is the 9th Army?

808
01:23:36.262 --> 01:23:41.100
Fourth. where will the 9th
Army break through?

809
01:23:41.726 --> 01:23:46.873
You'll see. gentlemen.
I'll be proven right.

810
01:23:47.148 --> 01:23:50.126
Wenck will come.

811
01:23:56.157 --> 01:23:59.202
Wenck will come.

812
01:24:11.631 --> 01:24:15.701
I want to know if it's possible
for Wenck to attack or not.

813
01:24:16.177 --> 01:24:21.007
It's unlikely that Wenck's small
force can attack the Red Army.

814
01:24:21.224 --> 01:24:23.326
How dare you say it's unlikely?

815
01:24:23.351 --> 01:24:26.012
Wenck has nothing to
confront the Red Army!

816
01:24:26.437 --> 01:24:29.207
Why don't you tell the Führer?

817
01:24:29.274 --> 01:24:32.794
Have you all gone crazy?
The Führer knows it himself!

818
01:24:32.819 --> 01:24:35.797
But he will never surrender!
And we won't either!

819
01:24:35.863 --> 01:24:38.733
I went through that before!
And once is enough!

820
01:24:38.741 --> 01:24:41.227
Come on. I have to
get out of here.

821
01:25:04.517 --> 01:25:06.728
Heil Hitler!

822
01:25:55.485 --> 01:25:58.321
Sorry. I fell asleep.

823
01:25:58.446 --> 01:26:01.457
So you rested up a bit. dear?

824
01:26:04.369 --> 01:26:07.129
Take it in shorthand.

825
01:26:12.377 --> 01:26:15.380
My political testament.

826
01:26:17.340 --> 01:26:22.387
Since 1914 when I invested
my modest strength in

827
01:26:22.553 --> 01:26:27.183
the First World War. which
was forced upon the Reich.

828
01:26:27.392 --> 01:26:31.062
over 30 years have passed.

829
01:26:31.729 --> 01:26:34.064
In those 3 decades.

830
01:26:34.065 --> 01:26:37.151
all my thoughts. actions. and my life

831
01:26:37.193 --> 01:26:42.031
were dictated by my love for
and loyalty to the German people.

832
01:26:44.158 --> 01:26:48.246
Sorry. but the heavy gunfire...
You sit there.

833
01:26:51.833 --> 01:26:54.519
Centuries will pass

834
01:26:55.086 --> 01:26:58.789
but from the ruins of our cities
and cultural monuments

835
01:26:59.757 --> 01:27:03.419
our hatred will be renewed
for those who are responsible

836
01:27:03.428 --> 01:27:08.407
for the people to whom
we owe all this:

837
01:27:08.474 --> 01:27:12.562
The international Jewry
and its supporters.

838
01:27:23.448 --> 01:27:26.451
What's wrong. Herr Minister?

839
01:27:29.203 --> 01:27:32.498
Imagine! The Führer wants
me to leave Berlin.

840
01:27:32.707 --> 01:27:35.626
He ordered me to leave.

841
01:27:37.253 --> 01:27:41.632
I've never disobeyed one of
the Führer orders. Never!

842
01:27:49.515 --> 01:27:55.521
But I will not obey this order.
I will stand by the Führer.

843
01:27:58.649 --> 01:28:02.820
I'm sorry. Frau Junge. but...

844
01:28:03.362 --> 01:28:06.791
I have to dictate my
personal testament to you.

845
01:28:08.409 --> 01:28:12.079
I'm typing the Führer testament.

846
01:28:12.830 --> 01:28:14.749
Fine.

847
01:28:15.541 --> 01:28:19.253
I understand.
I'll get back to you.

848
01:28:25.384 --> 01:28:27.094
My Führer. I...

849
01:28:27.261 --> 01:28:31.182
The Race Laws require
me to ask you this.

850
01:28:31.349 --> 01:28:34.801
My Führer. are you of
pure Aryan descent?

851
01:28:37.104 --> 01:28:41.692
Yes. May I see your ID?

852
01:28:42.443 --> 01:28:46.113
You're talking to the Führer.
Yes. sir.

853
01:28:46.322 --> 01:28:50.283
And are you. Frau Braun. of
pure Aryan descent? Yes

854
01:28:50.660 --> 01:28:53.979
Then the matter is...
there are no obstacles.

855
01:28:54.080 --> 01:28:58.142
I ask you: do you. my
Führer Adolf Hitler.

856
01:28:58.209 --> 01:29:03.230
take Eva Braun to be
your lawful wedded wife?

857
01:29:03.339 --> 01:29:05.341
Yes.

858
01:29:05.591 --> 01:29:09.545
Do you. Eva Braun. take
the Führer Adolf Hitler

859
01:29:09.554 --> 01:29:14.058
to be your lawful wedded
husband? Yes.

860
01:29:14.600 --> 01:29:18.104
I hereby declare you man and wife.

861
01:29:57.518 --> 01:30:00.187
I need two men!

862
01:30:01.355 --> 01:30:03.482
You'll be okay.

863
01:30:04.734 --> 01:30:08.379
The Führer wants to see you now.
At this hour?

864
01:30:27.214 --> 01:30:32.302
How long can you hold out?
Perhaps 20 hours. No longer.

865
01:30:33.137 --> 01:30:36.240
The Russians are just a
few hundred meters away.

866
01:30:36.349 --> 01:30:39.285
For the moment. we've stopped them.

867
01:30:39.310 --> 01:30:45.066
Know what. Mohnke? The Western
democracies are decadent.

868
01:30:45.232 --> 01:30:50.196
They will be defeated by those
disciplined people of the East.

869
01:30:53.282 --> 01:30:56.410
All the best.
Thank you.

870
01:30:56.702 --> 01:31:00.623
It wasn’t only for Germany.

871
01:31:20.434 --> 01:31:22.561
Keitel's report.

872
01:31:25.272 --> 01:31:29.034
"First. Wenck is stuck
south of Lake Schwielow.

873
01:31:29.110 --> 01:31:33.038
Second. the 12th Army cannot
continue its assault on Berlin.

874
01:31:33.447 --> 01:31:38.485
Third. the bulk of the
9th Army is encircled."

875
01:31:57.513 --> 01:32:02.727
My Führer. we need instructions
in case we run out of ammunition.

876
01:32:03.769 --> 01:32:07.806
I will never surrender.
Never.

877
01:32:08.649 --> 01:32:11.110
I forbid you to surrender.

878
01:32:11.277 --> 01:32:14.880
That goes for every other
commander as well.

879
01:32:25.791 --> 01:32:27.726
Listen. Günsche.

880
01:32:27.793 --> 01:32:33.340
Frau Braun. my wife. and
I will commit suicide.

881
01:32:33.549 --> 01:32:36.569
But I don't want the Russians to
exhibit my body in some museum.

882
01:32:36.635 --> 01:32:40.281
Don't let me fall into their
hands. dead or alive!

883
01:32:40.347 --> 01:32:45.703
I want my body to be burned
so it can never be found.

884
01:32:48.689 --> 01:32:52.076
Günsche. promise you will make
all necessary arrangements

885
01:32:52.109 --> 01:32:57.281
for the disposal of my mortal remains.

886
01:32:57.823 --> 01:33:00.576
My Führer...

887
01:33:00.785 --> 01:33:05.039
this is a terrible order.
but I will carry it out.

888
01:33:31.398 --> 01:33:33.976
Kempka. Erich. I need

889
01:33:34.068 --> 01:33:35.936
200 liters of gasoline.
<i>What?</i>

890
01:33:36.028 --> 01:33:38.339
Are you crazy? Where do
I get that much gasoline?

891
01:33:38.405 --> 01:33:41.300
From the parked vehicles.
No one needs them now.

892
01:33:41.367 --> 01:33:44.962
Why do you need so much gas?
I can't tell you on the phone.

893
01:34:01.428 --> 01:34:03.547
Come with me. please.

894
01:34:03.597 --> 01:34:06.567
The Führer wants to see us.

895
01:34:13.607 --> 01:34:17.027
Should I tell him you can't come?

896
01:34:17.278 --> 01:34:21.115
It's my pneumothorax.

897
01:34:22.199 --> 01:34:25.452
I won't last much longer anyway.

898
01:35:10.414 --> 01:35:13.042
Excuse me. Madam.

899
01:35:24.720 --> 01:35:27.723
This way. Professor.

900
01:35:36.357 --> 01:35:38.651
Please wait here.

901
01:35:48.035 --> 01:35:50.162
Excuse me...

902
01:36:23.070 --> 01:36:26.991
I'm sorry to interrupt
your important work.

903
01:36:27.157 --> 01:36:32.329
My Führer. preserve our
belief in the final victory!

904
01:36:32.496 --> 01:36:37.584
Lead us and we will follow you!

905
01:36:40.462 --> 01:36:42.131
Come on.

906
01:36:49.430 --> 01:36:52.725
Come in and join us!

907
01:36:54.059 --> 01:36:56.061
Here. have a drink.

908
01:36:57.771 --> 01:37:01.608
Drinking is all we have left.
Have a seat.

909
01:37:01.775 --> 01:37:03.610
That's better.

910
01:37:03.777 --> 01:37:09.399
Yes sir. our situation is hopeless.
It's what you call shitty!

911
01:37:13.037 --> 01:37:15.997
Be seated.
We are honored. Fräulein...

912
01:37:16.707 --> 01:37:20.352
Frau...
You may call me Frau Hitler.

913
01:37:23.172 --> 01:37:26.450
Don't worry. it's all right.

914
01:37:27.259 --> 01:37:33.006
Pity we can't go outside anymore.
Only if you want a hero's death.

915
01:37:33.766 --> 01:37:39.521
Fritz. pull yourself together!
Yes. sir! Pull myself together!

916
01:37:40.647 --> 01:37:42.775
Duck!

917
01:37:53.202 --> 01:37:56.062
That was a close call.

918
01:38:00.876 --> 01:38:02.669
Heil Hitler!

919
01:38:03.629 --> 01:38:07.449
Obersturmbannführer. what's up?
I must report to the Führer.

920
01:38:07.716 --> 01:38:09.976
Not now. Have a seat.

921
01:38:10.052 --> 01:38:12.471
Sit down. drink up.

922
01:38:16.350 --> 01:38:19.228
May I introduce you to Frau Hitler?

923
01:38:19.436 --> 01:38:24.024
So young and so many medals!
You must be proud of yourself.

924
01:38:26.193 --> 01:38:29.479
I must go. I'm not used
to drinking anymore.

925
01:38:29.488 --> 01:38:33.659
You can use our toilet.
Go ahead.

926
01:38:40.124 --> 01:38:45.587
If your hand shakes. the bullet
might only destroy the optic nerve.

927
01:38:45.796 --> 01:38:51.093
That's why it's advisable
to take poison too.

928
01:38:51.593 --> 01:38:56.465
Pull the trigger the moment
you bite the capsule.

929
01:38:56.473 --> 01:38:59.117
Will I have enough time to do it?

930
01:38:59.184 --> 01:39:03.179
The poison takes effect
after one or two seconds.

931
01:39:19.663 --> 01:39:22.349
Körner. you too.

932
01:40:04.416 --> 01:40:07.302
Frau Junge. I've known him.

933
01:40:07.753 --> 01:40:10.956
my husband. for over 15 years.

934
01:40:11.173 --> 01:40:16.061
But when I think about it.
I don't know anything about him.

935
01:40:16.386 --> 01:40:18.764
Although he likes to talk.

936
01:40:21.391 --> 01:40:26.647
I was looking forward to Berlin.
But he's changed so much.

937
01:40:26.813 --> 01:40:30.734
He only talks about dogs
and vegetarian meals.

938
01:40:30.776 --> 01:40:33.903
I really hate Blondi.

939
01:40:35.322 --> 01:40:40.986
Sometimes I kick her secretly. then
Adolf wonders about her behavior.

940
01:40:51.046 --> 01:40:54.624
It seems he doesn't want
anyone to see inside him.

941
01:40:54.675 --> 01:40:58.670
I mean deep inside.
In private.

942
01:40:59.680 --> 01:41:03.367
he can be such a caring person.

943
01:41:03.433 --> 01:41:08.188
But when he says...
such brutal things.

944
01:41:08.814 --> 01:41:12.167
When he's the Führer.

945
01:41:12.734 --> 01:41:16.238
Come on. let's have a smoke.

946
01:41:37.676 --> 01:41:39.736
I'm sorry.

947
01:41:41.096 --> 01:41:45.734
You've so many worries
and I sit here whining.

948
01:41:46.560 --> 01:41:50.455
Frau Junge. let me give you this
coat as a going-away present.

949
01:41:50.522 --> 01:41:53.417
I love well-dressed women.

950
01:41:53.442 --> 01:41:56.745
I want you to have
it and to enjoy it.

951
01:41:57.070 --> 01:42:00.607
What a surprise. Thank you.

952
01:42:00.824 --> 01:42:04.778
I have no idea where
and when I could wear it.

953
01:42:06.371 --> 01:42:10.542
Please. try to get out of here.

954
01:42:10.751 --> 01:42:13.712
Promise me.

955
01:43:42.008 --> 01:43:46.805
Thank you. that was very good.
Fräulein Manziarly.

956
01:44:08.076 --> 01:44:12.706
The time has come.
It's over now.

957
01:44:50.494 --> 01:44:53.288
The Führer wants to say farewell.

958
01:45:25.070 --> 01:45:28.281
You're the bravest mother
in the whole Reich.

959
01:45:28.490 --> 01:45:33.703
My Führer. you've made me
the happiest woman in Germany.

960
01:45:57.102 --> 01:45:59.646
Give my regards to Bavaria.

961
01:46:22.419 --> 01:46:27.507
Why are you here?
To see Aunt Eva and Uncle Hitler.

962
01:46:28.508 --> 01:46:33.096
Have you had anything to eat?
Just breakfast.

963
01:46:33.263 --> 01:46:36.624
I'll get you something to eat
and be right back. okay?

964
01:46:36.641 --> 01:46:38.602
Okay.

965
01:46:48.695 --> 01:46:51.715
Comrades. have you heard
the latest news from outside?

966
01:46:51.740 --> 01:46:54.175
Berlin's a city of warehouses.

967
01:46:54.242 --> 01:46:57.579
"Where's my house?
Where's my house?"

968
01:47:02.083 --> 01:47:05.011
Herr Günsche. I have
to see the Führer.

969
01:47:06.212 --> 01:47:07.631
Please!

970
01:47:07.797 --> 01:47:11.275
The Führer does not want
to be disturbed by anyone.

971
01:47:11.343 --> 01:47:14.829
Please. Günsche.
Just one moment.

972
01:47:15.096 --> 01:47:17.432
Please!

973
01:47:23.688 --> 01:47:26.816
My Führer. Frau Goebbels is here.

974
01:47:32.656 --> 01:47:33.898
What now?

975
01:47:34.783 --> 01:47:38.762
My Führer. I beg you leave Berlin!

976
01:47:39.371 --> 01:47:43.349
My Führer. please.
Don't leave us!

977
01:47:43.458 --> 01:47:46.386
What will become of us?

978
01:47:49.089 --> 01:47:52.734
Tomorrow. millions of
people will curse me

979
01:47:52.759 --> 01:47:56.671
but fate has taken its course.

980
01:47:59.099 --> 01:48:03.144
Get up. Come on.

981
01:48:04.104 --> 01:48:06.272
Come on.

982
01:48:14.364 --> 01:48:17.342
Aunt Traudl. I really
like those loud booms!

983
01:48:17.367 --> 01:48:22.455
Why?
Nothing can harm us here. right?

984
01:48:22.622 --> 01:48:24.340
You're right.

985
01:48:33.341 --> 01:48:35.134
Bullseye!

986
01:48:58.199 --> 01:49:01.536
Herr Reichsleiter. it has happened.

987
01:49:20.597 --> 01:49:23.224
The Führer is dead.

988
01:49:38.740 --> 01:49:41.117
There's Papa.

989
01:49:52.337 --> 01:49:56.466
Are you crazy?
That gasoline has caused...

990
01:49:56.633 --> 01:49:59.344
Be quiet. Erich.

991
01:50:09.354 --> 01:50:11.606
Step back!

992
01:50:24.077 --> 01:50:27.372
Come on! Come on!

993
01:51:54.375 --> 01:51:57.587
No! Don't!

994
01:52:01.382 --> 01:52:04.719
Let go of Grandma!

995
01:52:10.058 --> 01:52:15.188
Order... Order...

996
01:52:15.396 --> 01:52:18.691
Order must be restored!

997
01:52:26.366 --> 01:52:28.743
Go after those two!

998
01:52:32.205 --> 01:52:33.998
Here. this way!

999
01:52:34.165 --> 01:52:38.753
We know our way through the ruins!
Trust us! Hurry!

1000
01:52:44.342 --> 01:52:47.553
<font color="#808000"><i>I WAS ON THE SIDE
OF THE RED BEASTS</i></font>

1001
01:52:50.723 --> 01:52:53.518
<font color="#808000"><i>I SUPPORTED THE BOLSHEVIKS</i></font>

1002
01:53:01.025 --> 01:53:03.077
I hope the Russians got our message.

1003
01:53:03.152 --> 01:53:07.173
We'll know in a minute.
Or maybe not.

1004
01:53:11.077 --> 01:53:14.045
What news do you
bring us. General?

1005
01:53:14.539 --> 01:53:19.519
Hitler and his wife committed
suicide in the Führer's bunker.

1006
01:53:22.672 --> 01:53:25.099
The new government
has empowered me

1007
01:53:25.133 --> 01:53:28.594
to begin peace negotiations

1008
01:53:29.345 --> 01:53:32.281
between our two countries

1009
01:53:33.182 --> 01:53:38.563
which have suffered
the highest casualties.

1010
01:53:39.772 --> 01:53:44.694
General. would you want
peace in my position?

1011
01:53:45.153 --> 01:53:50.074
My government will not accept
an unconditional surrender.

1012
01:53:52.076 --> 01:53:56.797
Under these circumstances.
there's no other alternative.

1013
01:53:59.459 --> 01:54:02.645
We'll never surrender!
Outrageous!

1014
01:54:02.712 --> 01:54:05.481
I conquered Berlin against
the Reds years ago!

1015
01:54:05.548 --> 01:54:10.695
And I will defend it against
the Reds to my dying breath!

1016
01:54:10.720 --> 01:54:13.973
I won't use my final hours
as Reich Chancellor

1017
01:54:14.057 --> 01:54:18.411
to sign a statement of surrender!

1018
01:54:18.519 --> 01:54:21.706
We must protect civilians!
The Führer order is final!

1019
01:54:21.773 --> 01:54:26.477
Have you gone mad?
We have to negotiate.

1020
01:54:26.694 --> 01:54:28.337
I repeat. gentlemen:

1021
01:54:28.446 --> 01:54:32.675
I will never agree to surrender!
Telegraph Marshal Schukov.

1022
01:54:32.700 --> 01:54:34.594
Marshal Schukov?
What's going on?

1023
01:54:34.619 --> 01:54:37.062
This is crazy!
We must surrender to the Russians!

1024
01:54:37.080 --> 01:54:41.050
I'll shoot you! The Führer
forbade any kind of surrender!

1025
01:55:00.269 --> 01:55:04.432
How long does it last?
About four hours.

1026
01:55:20.206 --> 01:55:23.367
"Hansel crumbled his
bread in his pocket

1027
01:55:23.376 --> 01:55:27.688
and on their way into the forest.

1028
01:55:27.713 --> 01:55:30.274
he threw a morsel on the ground.

1029
01:55:30.299 --> 01:55:35.054
The woman led the children
still deeper into the forest

1030
01:55:35.179 --> 01:55:37.281
where they had never in
their lives been before.

1031
01:55:37.306 --> 01:55:39.142
Then a great fire was again made

1032
01:55:39.267 --> 01:55:40.785
and the mother said:
'Just sit there. you children"'

1033
01:55:40.852 --> 01:55:42.511
All right. children.

1034
01:55:42.603 --> 01:55:46.031
Dr. Stumpfegger has brought
the medicine I told you about.

1035
01:55:46.107 --> 01:55:49.193
It's bitter. but it's good for you.

1036
01:55:50.194 --> 01:55:53.239
Everyone gets a sip.

1037
01:55:53.614 --> 01:55:55.483
Who's first?

1038
01:55:58.327 --> 01:56:00.786
Heide. you're always so brave.

1039
01:56:07.712 --> 01:56:10.590
One more sip.

1040
01:56:12.508 --> 01:56:14.719
It wasn't that bad.

1041
01:56:20.099 --> 01:56:22.602
Good. Helmut?

1042
01:56:24.812 --> 01:56:26.063
Good.

1043
01:56:26.230 --> 01:56:29.942
It will keep you from getting
sick in this damp bunker.

1044
01:56:29.992 --> 01:56:33.412
But it isn't damp here.

1045
01:56:36.782 --> 01:56:39.118
Good. good.

1046
01:56:48.169 --> 01:56:50.213
Helga.

1047
01:56:52.256 --> 01:56:56.485
I don't want any.
Do you want to get sick?

1048
01:56:56.636 --> 01:57:00.014
Please. Mama. I don't want to.

1049
01:57:02.350 --> 01:57:06.562
Don't cry.
It won't help if you cry.

1050
01:57:07.271 --> 01:57:09.774
You have to drink it.

1051
01:57:12.818 --> 01:57:15.404
Helga!

1052
01:57:17.240 --> 01:57:23.454
Helga! Come on!
Open your mouth!

1053
01:57:23.663 --> 01:57:25.581
Papa!

1054
01:57:28.167 --> 01:57:31.254
Drink! Drink!

1055
01:57:43.808 --> 01:57:46.686
Sleep tight. children.

1056
01:57:56.237 --> 01:57:59.723
The lies will vanish one day

1057
01:57:59.782 --> 01:58:03.235
and light will brighten the darkness.

1058
01:58:03.286 --> 01:58:06.005
Would you read it to me. please?

1059
01:58:06.539 --> 01:58:11.419
"The lies will one day vanish and
light will brighten the darkness."

1060
01:58:12.378 --> 01:58:13.746
Let's do it again.

1061
01:58:13.754 --> 01:58:18.050
The lies will one day vanish
and above them

1062
01:58:18.217 --> 01:58:21.295
truth will once again triumph.

1063
01:58:21.429 --> 01:58:25.282
It will be the moment when
we stand above everything.

1064
01:58:25.349 --> 01:58:28.060
pure and...

1065
01:58:31.147 --> 01:58:32.840
unblemished.

1066
02:02:39.603 --> 02:02:43.457
We don't stand a chance.
I don't care. I want out.

1067
02:02:43.524 --> 02:02:48.078
How do we cross the Russian lines?
I won't stay a minute longer.

1068
02:02:48.153 --> 02:02:52.257
We're gonna die!
Stop it! It won't be so bad.

1069
02:02:52.324 --> 02:02:54.784
The Russians will get us if we stay.

1070
02:02:59.081 --> 02:03:01.667
Okay. let's go.

1071
02:04:30.130 --> 02:04:34.176
<i>On April 30. 1945.</i>

1072
02:04:34.301 --> 02:04:37.221
<i>the Führer committed suicide.</i>

1073
02:04:37.388 --> 02:04:42.434
<i>Thus. he abandoned all those
who had pledged allegiance to him.</i>

1074
02:04:42.726 --> 02:04:48.607
<i>German soldiers. you
obeyed the Führer orders</i>

1075
02:04:48.732 --> 02:04:54.571
<i>and were prepared to
continue the battle for Berlin</i>

1076
02:04:55.239 --> 02:04:58.200
<i>although you were running
out of ammunition.</i>

1077
02:04:58.325 --> 02:05:00.761
<i>and further resistance was futile.</i>

1078
02:05:00.828 --> 02:05:05.499
<i>I order an immediate cease-fire.</i>

1079
02:05:06.125 --> 02:05:09.011
<i>Every further hour of battle</i>

1080
02:05:09.086 --> 02:05:13.248
<i>will only prolong the civilians'
terrible suffering</i>

1081
02:05:13.465 --> 02:05:16.359
<i>and the suffering of our wounded.</i>

1082
02:05:16.385 --> 02:05:20.405
<i>In agreement with the Soviet
Army Supreme Command.</i>

1083
02:05:20.472 --> 02:05:22.533
<i>I order you</i>

1084
02:05:22.599 --> 02:05:26.470
<i>to cease fighting at once!</i>

1085
02:05:26.603 --> 02:05:28.147
Weidling.

1086
02:05:28.313 --> 02:05:30.624
former Commanding Officer

1087
02:05:30.691 --> 02:05:33.977
of the Berlin Defense Force.

1088
02:05:35.738 --> 02:05:38.674
A glass of water. please.

1089
02:06:43.555 --> 02:06:46.566
I no longer need you.

1090
02:06:49.353 --> 02:06:51.730
The die is cast.

1091
02:07:59.423 --> 02:08:02.759
It's time. Doctor.
You see how busy we are.

1092
02:08:03.051 --> 02:08:06.054
I insist that you accompany us.

1093
02:08:07.306 --> 02:08:09.474
So that's it.

1094
02:08:16.398 --> 02:08:18.442
Go on.

1095
02:08:18.567 --> 02:08:22.362
You've done a great deal.
Thank you.

1096
02:08:28.577 --> 02:08:29.870
Schädle. come with me.

1097
02:08:30.537 --> 02:08:34.499
Sorry. I'm not going anywhere.

1098
02:08:36.168 --> 02:08:38.545
Let's go!

1099
02:09:56.039 --> 02:09:59.418
Sturmmann Krüger gets
the Iron Cross. 2nd class

1100
02:09:59.543 --> 02:10:02.546
for defending Wolf Bridge.

1101
02:10:03.005 --> 02:10:06.007
Wagner took out 2 machine-gun posts

1102
02:10:06.008 --> 02:10:07.959
and defended Puttkammerstrasse.

1103
02:10:08.051 --> 02:10:11.438
He gets the Iron Cross.
2nd class.

1104
02:10:11.638 --> 02:10:15.008
Sturmmann Rauch gets
the Iron Cross

1105
02:10:15.142 --> 02:10:18.528
for helping messengers
get through enemy lines.

1106
02:10:49.760 --> 02:10:51.736
The others!

1107
02:10:56.224 --> 02:10:58.060
Oh. God!

1108
02:11:01.313 --> 02:11:04.107
Get outta here!
Hurry!

1109
02:11:06.485 --> 02:11:08.153
Help!

1110
02:11:19.790 --> 02:11:21.850
Who goes there?

1111
02:11:28.757 --> 02:11:30.717
A German.

1112
02:11:36.473 --> 02:11:38.433
Herr Hewel?

1113
02:11:39.476 --> 02:11:43.522
Hewel. thank God you're alive.

1114
02:11:45.732 --> 02:11:48.276
Where are the others?

1115
02:11:50.153 --> 02:11:54.324
I don't know. Frau Junge.
Somewhere... perhaps.

1116
02:11:54.533 --> 02:11:58.120
I'm sure most of the people
in my group are dead.

1117
02:11:58.370 --> 02:12:01.623
I never should have left the bunker.

1118
02:12:01.748 --> 02:12:04.209
I should have shot myself.

1119
02:12:05.502 --> 02:12:08.088
But I couldn't.

1120
02:12:08.255 --> 02:12:12.801
Eat something.
There's time enough to die.

1121
02:13:01.600 --> 02:13:03.643
Attention!

1122
02:13:09.107 --> 02:13:11.234
Stay with the women.

1123
02:13:12.569 --> 02:13:14.613
Come here.

1124
02:13:26.249 --> 02:13:28.242
The Russians have us surrounded.

1125
02:13:28.251 --> 02:13:30.420
What will we do?

1126
02:13:30.629 --> 02:13:33.715
You can try to get through.

1127
02:13:34.049 --> 02:13:36.142
I'm not taking another step.

1128
02:13:37.010 --> 02:13:41.723
Think it over. The Russians 
are only after us.

1129
02:13:42.015 --> 02:13:44.768
As women. you have a chance.

1130
02:13:45.060 --> 02:13:47.145
Give it a try.

1131
02:13:47.812 --> 02:13:50.232
Good luck.

1132
02:13:52.317 --> 02:13:56.780
When you go past the Russians.
don't look anybody in the eye.

1133
02:13:57.239 --> 02:13:59.282
Don't forget.

1134
02:13:59.449 --> 02:14:00.784
Good luck.

1135
02:14:09.501 --> 02:14:10.669
The Russians!

1136
02:14:23.306 --> 02:14:26.309
Let's go.
Go ahead.

1137
02:14:27.060 --> 02:14:29.604
I can't go on.
Please.

1138
02:14:31.690 --> 02:14:36.278
I have to try.
Don't be angry with me.

1139
02:14:40.282 --> 02:14:42.492
I'll manage.

1140
02:14:55.255 --> 02:14:56.673
Doctor!

1141
02:14:57.090 --> 02:14:58.842
Herr Doctor!

1142
02:14:59.134 --> 02:15:02.303
My comrades want to surrender
to the Russians. May I join you?

1143
02:15:02.387 --> 02:15:03.805
The Führer is dead.

1144
02:15:04.097 --> 02:15:08.726
You want to fight the war alone?
I feel committed to my oath.

1145
02:15:08.727 --> 02:15:13.023
Then talk to the Brigadeführer.

1146
02:15:42.093 --> 02:15:43.813
The Russians are clearing 
the area. Yes?

1147
02:15:43.845 --> 02:15:46.506
No resistance.
No shots have been fired.

1148
02:15:46.598 --> 02:15:49.759
They'll be here in an hour.

1149
02:15:50.101 --> 02:15:52.395
What should we do?

1150
02:15:52.562 --> 02:15:55.231
Our honor won't allow us to surrender!

1151
02:15:55.273 --> 02:15:57.225
What does that mean?

1152
02:15:57.275 --> 02:16:01.129
When the Russians come.
we fire until we're out of bullets.

1153
02:16:01.196 --> 02:16:03.489
Then we blow our brains out.

1154
02:16:03.531 --> 02:16:05.508
Rubbish!

1155
02:16:05.533 --> 02:16:10.455
Is this murderous. suicidal killing
for prestige the only way out?

1156
02:16:10.789 --> 02:16:15.085
We're SS officers. We can't 
outlive the Führer death!

1157
02:16:15.251 --> 02:16:17.604
Who else feels that way?

1158
02:18:05.153 --> 02:18:09.482
Want to sit with me a moment?
I'd love to.

1159
02:18:14.287 --> 02:18:16.255
Why do you want to go on living?

1160
02:18:16.331 --> 02:18:21.085
And why do you want to die?

1161
02:18:21.294 --> 02:18:23.046
See this?

1162
02:18:23.713 --> 02:18:26.724
The Führer himself gave it to me.

1163
02:18:27.300 --> 02:18:29.819
A final decoration?

1164
02:18:30.053 --> 02:18:34.390
Perhaps. Hitler gave it
to me at his farewell.

1165
02:18:34.557 --> 02:18:38.228
He made me swear a vow.

1166
02:18:38.394 --> 02:18:42.832
That I would kill myself the moment
the Russians captured me.

1167
02:18:43.274 --> 02:18:46.711
Hitler made you promise
to kill yourself?

1168
02:18:46.820 --> 02:18:49.272
But why?
He probably

1169
02:18:49.280 --> 02:18:53.943
didn't want me to be forced
to speak negatively of him.

1170
02:18:54.160 --> 02:18:59.032
But as a diplomat. you are
protected by international law.

1171
02:18:59.123 --> 02:19:03.136
Who will benefit if you
keep your promise?

1172
02:19:03.169 --> 02:19:05.563
They're here!

1173
02:19:17.767 --> 02:19:21.145
Don't shoot. comrades!

1174
02:19:23.356 --> 02:19:26.167
We have surrendered.

1175
02:19:26.234 --> 02:19:28.278
The war is over.

1176
02:19:29.362 --> 02:19:31.489
It's over.

1177
02:21:04.457 --> 02:21:06.751
<font color="#808000">GERMANY OFFICIALLY SURRENDERED</font>

1178
02:21:07.043 --> 02:21:08.461
<font color="#808000">ON MAY 7. 1945</font>

1179
02:21:09.671 --> 02:21:12.090
<font color="#808000">IT WAS AGREED THAT ALL HOSTILITIES</font>

1180
02:21:12.256 --> 02:21:13.633
<font color="#808000">END AT MIDNIGHT. MAY 8.</font>

1181
02:21:14.759 --> 02:21:17.637
<font color="#808000">BY THEN. THE WAR HAD COST</font>

1182
02:21:17.804 --> 02:21:19.347
<font color="#808000">OVER 50 MILLION LIVES.</font>

1183
02:21:20.223 --> 02:21:23.685
<font color="#808000">6 MILLIONS JEWS HAD BEEN MURDERED</font>

1184
02:21:24.018 --> 02:21:26.312
<font color="#808000">IN GERMAN CONCENTRATION CAMPS</font>

1185
02:21:26.729 --> 02:21:30.483
<font color="#808000">WAS ABLE TO ESCAPE AND
AVOIDED IMPRISONMENT.</font>

1186
02:21:30.650 --> 02:21:35.405
<font color="#808000">SHE DIED IN DUSSELDORF
ON APRIL 14. 1997.</font>

1187
02:21:35.697 --> 02:21:39.158
<font color="#808000">RELIEVED FROM SOVIET CAPTIVITY IN 1953.</font>

1188
02:21:39.325 --> 02:21:44.288
<font color="#808000">HE DIED IN AACHEN ON DECEMBER 21. 1998.</font>

1189
02:21:44.497 --> 02:21:48.292
<font color="#808000">RELIEVED FROM SOVIET CAPTIVITY IN 1955.</font>

1190
02:21:48.459 --> 02:21:52.714
<font color="#808000">HE DIED IN DAMP. NEAR ECKERNFÖRDE
ON AUGUST 6. 2001.</font>

1191
02:21:53.089 --> 02:21:59.637
<font color="#808000">DIED IN SOVIET CAPTIVITY IN 1955.</font>

1192
02:21:59.804 --> 02:22:04.350
<font color="#808000">ARRESTED BY THE RED ARMY IN
THE MILITARY HOSPITAL BUNKER.</font>

1193
02:22:04.517 --> 02:22:09.063
<font color="#808000">HE DIED IN SOVIET CAPTIVITY IN 1945.</font>

1194
02:22:09.230 --> 02:22:11.649
<font color="#808000">CAPTURED BY THE SOVIETS AND
RELEASED FROM BAUTZEN PRISON</font>

1195
02:22:11.816 --> 02:22:14.485
<font color="#808000">IN EAST GERMANY. IN MAY 1956</font>

1196
02:22:14.694 --> 02:22:17.655
<font color="#808000">HE DIED IN LOHMAR.
NEAR BONN. IN 2003.</font>

1197
02:22:18.031 --> 02:22:20.533
<font color="#808000">SURVIVED THE WAR
AND WENT ON TO SET</font>

1198
02:22:20.700 --> 02:22:23.036
<font color="#808000">MANY WORLD FLYING RECORDS.</font>

1199
02:22:23.202 --> 02:22:25.872
<font color="#808000">SHE DIED ON AUGUST 28. 1978.</font>

1200
02:22:26.205 --> 02:22:31.544
<font color="#808000">COMMITTED SUICIDE IN SALZBURG
ON MAY 24. 1945.</font>

1201
02:22:31.753 --> 02:22:33.755
<font color="#808000">WERE CAPTURED BY THE SOVIETS.</font>

1202
02:22:34.088 --> 02:22:36.382
<font color="#808000">LINGE WAS RELEASED IN 1955.
HE DIED IN BREMEN IN 1980.</font>

1203
02:22:36.549 --> 02:22:38.760
<font color="#808000">HENTSCHEL WAS RELEASED IN 1949.</font>

1204
02:22:39.052 --> 02:22:41.429
<font color="#808000">HE DIED IN ACHERN ON APRIL 27. 1982.</font>

1205
02:22:41.804 --> 02:22:46.184
<font color="#808000">VANISHED WITHOUT A TRACE IN BERLIN</font>

1206
02:22:46.350 --> 02:22:48.436
<font color="#808000">DURING HER ESCAPE.</font>

1207
02:22:48.811 --> 02:22:51.147
<font color="#808000">ARRESTED IN FLENSBURG IN 1945.</font>

1208
02:22:51.355 --> 02:22:53.483
<font color="#808000">HE WAS SENTENCED TO 20 YEARS</font>

1209
02:22:53.691 --> 02:22:56.444
<font color="#808000">AT THE NUREMBERG TRIAL AND
WAS RELEASED IN 1966.</font>

1210
02:22:56.611 --> 02:22:58.488
<font color="#808000">HE DIED IN LONDON IN 1981.</font>

1211
02:22:58.780 --> 02:23:02.366
<font color="#808000">SENTENCED TO DEATH</font>

1212
02:23:02.575 --> 02:23:05.787
<font color="#808000">AT THE NUREMBERG TRIAL
AND EXECUTED.</font>

1213
02:23:06.204 --> 02:23:08.790
<font color="#808000">SENTENCED TO DEATH.
COMMITTED SUICIDE IN PRISON</font>

1214
02:23:09.123 --> 02:23:12.752
<font color="#808000">BEFORE THE EXECUTION WAS CARRIED OUT.</font>

1215
02:23:13.503 --> 02:23:15.463
<font color="#808000">TRIED TO ESCAPE WITH A FALSE IDENTITY</font>

1216
02:23:15.630 --> 02:23:17.465
<font color="#808000">WITH OTHER FLEEING REFUGEES.</font>

1217
02:23:17.632 --> 02:23:21.719
<font color="#808000">AFTER BEING EXPOSED AND
CAPTURED. COMMITTED SUICIDE.</font>

1218
02:23:22.053 --> 02:23:26.682
<font color="#808000">COMMITTED SUICIDE NEAR
LEHRTER TRAIN STATION</font>

1219
02:23:27.016 --> 02:23:31.062
<font color="#808000">ON THE MORNING OF MAY 2. 1945.</font>

1220
02:23:31.229 --> 02:23:35.441
<font color="#808000">RELEASED FROM SOVIET CAPTIVITY IN 1955.</font>

1221
02:23:35.608 --> 02:23:38.402
<font color="#808000">HE NOW LIVES IN BERLIN.</font>

1222
02:23:38.611 --> 02:23:41.197
<font color="#808000">CLASSIFIED BY THE WESTERN
ALLIES AS A "YOUNG FOLLOWER"</font>

1223
02:23:41.364 --> 02:23:44.117
<font color="#808000">SHE CONTINUED TO WORK AS A
SECRETARY FOR VARIOUS COMPANIES</font>

1224
02:23:44.242 --> 02:23:45.551
<font color="#808000">AND LIVED IN MUNICH
UNTIL HER DEATH IN 2002.</font>

1225
02:23:45.618 --> 02:23:48.745
Of course. the terrible things

1226
02:23:48.746 --> 02:23:51.623
I heard from the Nuremberg Trials

1227
02:23:51.624 --> 02:23:57.547
about the 6 millions Jews
and the people of other races.

1228
02:23:57.713 --> 02:23:59.714
who were killed.

1229
02:23:59.715 --> 02:24:04.637
were facts that shocked me deeply.

1230
02:24:05.263 --> 02:24:10.351
But I wasn't able to see the
connection with my own past.

1231
02:24:10.518 --> 02:24:15.731
I was satisfied that I wasn't
personally to blame

1232
02:24:16.065 --> 02:24:21.445
and that I hadn't known
about those things.

1233
02:24:21.612 --> 02:24:23.823
I wasn't aware of the extent.
But one day.

1234
02:24:24.157 --> 02:24:28.286
I went past the memorial plaque

1235
02:24:28.494 --> 02:24:32.123
which had been put up for Sophie
Scholl in Franz Josef Strasse

1236
02:24:32.248 --> 02:24:36.377
and I saw that she was born
the same year as me.

1237
02:24:36.544 --> 02:24:42.508
and she was executed the same
year I started working for Hitler.

1238
02:24:42.717 --> 02:24:45.636
And at that moment.

1239
02:24:45.803 --> 02:24:51.684
I actually sensed that it was
no excuse to be young.

1240
02:24:52.059 --> 02:24:55.062
and that it would
have been possible

1241
02:24:55.271 --> 02:24:57.648
to find things out.

1242
02:24:58.672 --> 02:25:02.672
